msgstr "Opdel kontakter i specifikke mailinglister."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:22
msgid "Manage unsubscriptions (Blacklist)"
msgstr "Administrer afmeldinger (sortliste)"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:22
msgid "Allow recipients to unsubscribe and blacklist from future mailings."
msgstr ""
"Giv modtagere mulighed for at afmelde sig og blive sat på sortliste for "
"fremtidige udsendelser."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:27
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:3
msgid "Lost leads reactivation email"
msgstr "E-mail til genaktivering af tabte kundeemner"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:27
msgid "Target lost leads with Email Marketing."
msgstr "Målret tabte leads med e-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:32
msgid "Analyze Metrics"
msgstr "Analyser målepunkter"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:32
msgid "Analyzing campaign metrics."
msgstr "Analysering af kampagnemålepunkter."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:38
msgid "Email marketing dashboard"
msgstr "Dashboard til e-mailmarketing"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:40
msgid ""
"After installing the application, click the :menuselection:`Email Marketing` "
"app icon from the main Odoo dashboard. Doing so reveals the "
"main :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard in the default list view."
msgstr ""
"Efter installation af applikationen klikkes på :menuselection:`E-"
"mailmarketing`-app-ikonet fra Odoos hoveddashboard. Dette viser "
"hoveddashboardet :guilabel:`Udsendelser` i standardlistevisningen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the main dashboard of the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr "Visning af hoveddashboardet i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:47
msgid ""
"In the search bar, the default filter of :guilabel:`My Mailings` is present "
"to show all the mailings related to the current user. To remove that filter, "
"click the :guilabel:`✖️ (remove)` icon next to the filter in the search bar. "
"Doing so reveals all the mailings in the database."
msgstr ""
"I søgefeltet er standardfilteret :guilabel:`Mine udsendelser` til stede for "
"at vise alle udsendelser relateret til den aktuelle bruger. For at fjerne "
"dette filter klikkes på ikonet :guilabel:`✖️ (fjern)` ved siden af filteret "
"i søgefeltet. Dette viser alle udsendelser i databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:51
msgid ""
"The information on the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard has four different "
"view options, located in the upper-right corner as individual icons."
msgstr ""
"Informationen på dashboardet :guilabel:`Udsendelser` har fire forskellige "
"visningsmuligheder, placeret i øverste højre hjørne som individuelle ikoner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:54
msgid "The view options, from left-to-right, are:"
msgstr "Visningsmuligheder, fra venstre til højre, er:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:56
msgid ":ref:`List <email_marketing/list-view>` (default view)"
msgstr ":ref:`Liste <email_marketing/list-view>` (standardvisning)"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:57
msgid ":ref:`Kanban <email_marketing/kanban-view>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Kanban <email_marketing/kanban-view>`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:58
msgid ":ref:`Calendar <email_marketing/calendar-view>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Kalender <email_marketing/calendar-view>`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:59
msgid ":ref:`Graph <email_marketing/graph-view>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Graf <email_marketing/graph-view>`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:64
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:736
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/social_marketing/social_posts.rst:52
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/surveys.rst:172
msgid "List view"
msgstr "Listevisning"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:66
msgid ""
"The list view, represented by the :guilabel:`☰ (horizontal lines)` icon in "
"the upper-right corner, is the default view of the :guilabel:`Mailings` "
"dashboard in the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app."
msgstr ""
"Listevisningen, repræsenteret af ikonet :guilabel:`☰ (vandrette linjer)` i "
"øvre højre hjørne, er standardvisningen af :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboardet "
"i :guilabel:`E-mailmarketing` appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:69
msgid ""
"While in list view, there are columns dedicated to different aspects of "
"information related to the listed emails. Those columns are as follows:"
msgstr ""
"I listevisning er der kolonner dedikeret til forskellige aspekter af "
"information relateret til de listede e-mails. Disse kolonner er følgende:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:72
msgid ":guilabel:`Date`: the date the email was sent."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Dato`: datoen hvor e-mailen blev sendt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:73
msgid ":guilabel:`Subject`: the subject of the email."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Emne`: emnet for e-mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:74
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Responsible`: the user who created the email, or the user who has "
"been assigned to the email."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Ansvarlig`: brugeren der oprettede e-mailen, eller brugeren der "
"er blevet tildelt e-mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:76
msgid ":guilabel:`Sent`: how many times the email has been sent."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Sendt`: hvor mange gange e-mailen er blevet sendt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:77
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Delivered (%)`: percentage of sent emails that have been "
"successfully delivered."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Leveret (%)`: procentdel af sendte e-mails der er blevet leveret."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:78
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Opened (%)`: percentage of sent emails that have been opened by "
"the recipients."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Åbnet (%)`: procentdel af sendte e-mails der er blevet åbnet af "
"modtagerne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:79
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Clicked (%)`: percentage of sent emails that have been clicked by "
"the recipients."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Klikket (%)`: procentdel af sendte e-mails der er blevet klikket "
"på af modtagerne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:80
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Replied (%)`: percentage of sent emails that have been replied to "
"by the recipients."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Besvaret (%)`: procentdel af sendte e-mails der er blevet "
"besvaret af modtagerne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:81
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Status`: the status of the email "
"(:guilabel:`Draft`, :guilabel:`In Queue`, or :guilabel:`Sent`)."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Status`: status for e-mailen (:guilabel:`Kladde`, :guilabel:`I "
"kø` eller :guilabel:`Sendt`)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:84
msgid ""
"To add or remove columns, click the :guilabel:`Additional Options (two "
"horizontal lines with dots)` icon, located to the far-right of the column "
"titles in list view. Doing so reveals a drop-down menu of additional column "
"options."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje eller fjerne kolonner skal du klikke på ikonet "
":guilabel:`Yderligere indstillinger (to vandrette linjer med prikker)`, som "
"findes til højre for kolonnetitlerne i listevisning. Dette åbner en "
"rullemenu med yderligere kolonnemuligheder."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:91
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:709
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/social_marketing/social_posts.rst:23
msgid "Kanban view"
msgstr "Kanban-visning"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:93
msgid ""
"The Kanban view, represented by the :guilabel:`(inverted bar graph)` icon, "
"can be accessed in the upper-right corner of the :guilabel:`Mailings` "
"dashboard in the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app."
msgstr ""
"Kanban-visningen, repræsenteret af ikonet :guilabel:`(omvendt søjlediagram)"
"`, kan tilgås i øvre højre hjørne af :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboardet i "
":guilabel:`E-mailmarketing` appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"Kanban view of the main dashboard of the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr ""
"Kanban-visning af hoveddashboardet i Odoo E-mailmarketing applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:100
msgid ""
"While in Kanban view, the email information is displayed in the various "
"stages."
msgstr "I Kanban-visning vises e-mailinformationen i de forskellige stadier."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:102
msgid ""
"The stages are: :guilabel:`Draft`, :guilabel:`In "
"Queue`, :guilabel:`Sending`, and :guilabel:`Sent`."
msgstr ""
"Stadierne er: :guilabel:`Kladde`, :guilabel:`I kø`, :guilabel:`Sender` og "
":guilabel:`Sendt`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:104
msgid ":guilabel:`Draft`: the email is still being written/created."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Kladde`: e-mailen skrives/oprettes stadig."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:105
msgid ""
":guilabel:`In Queue`: the email is scheduled to be sent at a later date."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`I kø`: e-mailen er planlagt til at blive sendt på en senere dato."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:106
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Sending`: the email is currently being sent to its recipients."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Sender`: e-mailen sendes i øjeblikket til sine modtagere."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:107
msgid ":guilabel:`Sent`: the email has already been sent to its recipients."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Sendt`: e-mailen er allerede sendt til modtagerne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:109
msgid ""
"In each stage, there are drag-and-drop cards representing the emails that "
"have been created/sent, and the stage they are in represents the current "
"status of that mailing."
msgstr ""
"I hvert stadie er der kort, der kan trækkes og slippes, som repræsenterer de "
"e-mails, der er oprettet/sendt, og stadiet, de befinder sig i, repræsenterer "
"den aktuelle status for den udsendelse."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:112
msgid ""
"Each card on the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard provides key information "
"related to that specific email."
msgstr ""
"Hvert kort på :guilabel:`Mailings`-dashboardet viser nøgleinformationer "
"relateret til den specifikke e-mail."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:115
msgid ""
"When the cursor hovers over the upper-right corner of an email campaign "
"card, a :guilabel:`⋮ (three vertical dots)` icon appears. When clicked, a "
"mini drop-down menu reveals the option to color-code the "
"email, :guilabel:`Delete` the email, or :guilabel:`Archive` the message for "
"potential future use."
msgstr ""
"Når markøren svæver over øverste højre hjørne af et e-mailkampagnekort, "
"vises et :guilabel:`⋮ (tre lodrette prikker)`-ikon. Når der klikkes på det, "
"viser en lille rullemenu muligheden for at farvekode e-mailen, "
":guilabel:`Slet` e-mailen eller :guilabel:`Arkiver` beskeden til potentiel "
"fremtidig brug."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of the three-dot drop-down menu on the Odoo Email Marketing dashboard."
msgstr ""
"Visning af rullemenu med tre prikker på Odoo E-mailmarketing-dashboardet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:127
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/social_marketing/social_posts.rst:36
msgid "Calendar view"
msgstr "Kalendervisning"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:129
msgid ""
"The calendar view, represented by a :guilabel:`📆 (calendar)` icon, can be "
"accessed in the upper-right corner of the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard in "
"the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app."
msgstr ""
"Kalendervisningen, repræsenteret ved et :guilabel:`📆 (kalender)`-ikon, kan "
"tilgås i øverste højre hjørne af :guilabel:`Mailings`-dashboardet i "
":guilabel:`E-mailmarketing`-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:132
msgid ""
"While in calendar view, a monthly calendar (by default), shows when the "
"mailings have been sent or are scheduled to be sent."
msgstr ""
"I kalendervisning viser en månedskalender (som standard), hvornår "
"udsendelserne er sendt eller planlagt til at blive sendt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"Calendar view of the mailings dashboard in the Email Marketing application."
msgstr ""
"Kalendervisning af mailings-dashboardet i E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:139
msgid ""
"The current date is represented by a :guilabel:`🔴 (red circle)` icon over "
"the date on the calendar."
msgstr ""
"Den aktuelle dato er repræsenteret ved et :guilabel:`🔴 (rød cirkel)`-ikon "
"over datoen på kalenderen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:141
msgid ""
"To the right of the calendar, the options to filter the results "
"by :guilabel:`Responsible` and/or :guilabel:`Status` are available, via "
"checkboxes."
msgstr ""
"Til højre for kalenderen er mulighederne for at filtrere resultaterne efter "
":guilabel:`Ansvarlig` og/eller :guilabel:`Status` tilgængelige via "
"afkrydsningsfelter."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:145
msgid ""
"To hide the right sidebar, click the :guilabel:`(panel-right)` icon, located "
"above the sidebar."
msgstr ""
"For at skjule højre sidepanel skal du klikke på :guilabel:`(panel-right)`-"
"ikonet, som findes over sidepanelet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:147
msgid ""
"In the top-left corner, above the calendar, the option to change the time "
"period being displayed is available via a drop-down menu, which "
"shows :guilabel:`Month`, by default. When clicked, the drop-down menu that "
"appears reveals the "
"options: :guilabel:`Day`, :guilabel:`Week`, :guilabel:`Month` "
"(default), :guilabel:`Year`, and :guilabel:`Show weekends` (selected by "
"default)."
msgstr ""
"I øverste venstre hjørne over kalenderen er muligheden for at ændre den "
"viste tidsperiode tilgængelig via en rullemenu, som viser :guilabel:`Måned` "
"som standard. Når der klikkes på den, viser rullemenuet, der vises, "
"mulighederne: :guilabel:`Dag`, :guilabel:`Uge`, :guilabel:`Måned` (standard)"
", :guilabel:`År` og :guilabel:`Vis weekender` (valgt som standard)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:152
msgid ""
"Clicking any of those options changes the calendar display to reflect that "
"desired amount of time."
msgstr ""
"Klik på en af disse muligheder ændrer kalendervisningen, så den afspejler "
"den ønskede tidsperiode."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:154
msgid ""
"Clicking either :guilabel:`⬅️ (left arrow)` icon or :guilabel:`➡️ (right "
"arrow)` icon changes the calendar to a previous or future time, depending on "
"what is clicked, based on the chosen amount of time being represented."
msgstr ""
"Klik på enten :guilabel:`⬅️ (venstre pil)`-ikonet eller :guilabel:`➡️ (højre "
"pil)`-ikonet ændrer kalenderen til en tidligere eller fremtidig tid, "
"afhængigt af hvad der klikkes på, baseret på den valgte tidsperiode, der "
"repræsenteres."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:158
msgid "To jump back to the current date, click the :guilabel:`Today` button."
msgstr ""
"For at springe tilbage til den aktuelle dato skal du klikke på knappen "
":guilabel:`I dag`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:163
msgid "Graph view"
msgstr "Grafové zobrazení"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:165
msgid ""
"The graph view, represented by a :guilabel:`(line graph)` icon, can be "
"accessed in the upper-right corner of the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard in "
"the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app."
msgstr ""
"Grafvisningen, repræsenteret ved et :guilabel:`(linjegraf)`-ikon, kan tilgås "
"i øverste højre hjørne af :guilabel:`Mailings`-dashboardet i :guilabel:`E-"
"mailmarketing`-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:168
msgid ""
"While in graph view, the status of the emails on the :guilabel:`Mailings` "
"page is represented in a bar graph, but other graph view options can be "
"implemented, if needed."
msgstr ""
"I grafvisning repræsenteres status for e-mails på :guilabel:`Mailings`-siden "
"i et søjlediagram, men andre grafvisningsmuligheder kan implementeres, hvis "
"det er nødvendigt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "How the Graph view appears in the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr "Sådan ser grafvisningen ud i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:175
msgid ""
"In the upper-left corner, above the graph, there is a :guilabel:`Measures` "
"drop-down menu. When clicked, different filter options become available to "
"further customize the graph views."
msgstr ""
"I øverste venstre hjørne over grafen er der en :guilabel:`Målinger`-"
"rullemenu. Når der klikkes på den, bliver forskellige filtermuligheder "
"tilgængelige for yderligere at tilpasse grafvisningerne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:178
msgid ""
"Those :guilabel:`Measures` options are: :guilabel:`A/B Testing percentage` "
"and :guilabel:`Count` (default)."
msgstr ""
"Disse :guilabel:`Målinger` muligheder er: :guilabel:`A/B-testprocent` og "
":guilabel:`Antal` (standard)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:181
msgid ""
"To the right of the :guilabel:`Measures` drop-down menu is "
"an :guilabel:`Insert in Spreadsheet` button, if the *Documents* application "
"is installed. When clicked, a pop-up window appears, in which the ability to "
"add the graph to a spreadsheet or dashboard becomes available."
msgstr ""
"Til højre for rullemenuen :guilabel:`Målinger` er der en :guilabel:`Indsæt i "
"regneark` knap, hvis programmet *Dokumenter* er installeret. Når der "
"klikkes, vises et pop-op-vindue, hvor muligheden for at tilføje grafen til "
"et regneark eller dashboard bliver tilgængelig."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:185
msgid ""
"Beside the :guilabel:`Measures` drop-down menu and :guilabel:`Insert in "
"Spreadsheet` button are different graph view options. From left-to-right, "
"those graph view options are: :guilabel:`(bar chart)` "
"(default), :guilabel:`(line chart)`, and :guilabel:`(pie chart)`."
msgstr ""
"Ved siden af rullemenuen :guilabel:`Målinger` og knappen :guilabel:`Indsæt i "
"regneark` er der forskellige grafvisningsmuligheder. Fra venstre mod højre "
"er disse grafvisningsmuligheder: :guilabel:`(søjlediagram)` (standard), "
":guilabel:`(linjediagram)` og :guilabel:`(cirkeldiagram)`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:190
msgid ""
"Each graph view option provides its own series of additional view options, "
"which appear to the right of the selected graph view option."
msgstr ""
"Hver grafvisningsmulighed giver sine egne serier af yderligere "
"visningsmuligheder, som vises til højre for den valgte grafvisningsmulighed."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:194
msgid "Search options"
msgstr "Søgemuligheder"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:196
msgid ""
"Regardless of the view chosen for the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard in "
"the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app, "
"the :guilabel:`Filters`, :guilabel:`Group by`, and :guilabel:`Favorites` "
"options are always available to further customize the information being "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
"Uanset hvilken visning der er valgt til :guilabel:`Udsendelser` dashboardet "
"i :guilabel:`E-mailmarketing` appen, er mulighederne :guilabel:`Filtre`, "
":guilabel:`Gruppér efter` og :guilabel:`Favoritter` altid tilgængelige til "
"yderligere at tilpasse de oplysninger, der vises."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:200
msgid ""
"To access those options, click the :guilabel:`(downward arrow)` icon, "
"located to the right of the search bar. Doing so reveals a drop-down mega "
"menu featuring those filtering and grouping options."
msgstr ""
"For at få adgang til disse muligheder skal du klikke på ikonet :guilabel:`"
"(pil nedad)`, som er placeret til højre for søgefeltet. Dette afslører en "
"rullemegamenu med disse filtrerings- og grupperingsmuligheder."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"The drop-down mega menu of search options the Odoo Email Marketing "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Rullemegamenuen med søgemuligheder i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:207
msgid ""
"These options provide various ways to specify and organize the information "
"seen on the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard."
msgstr ""
"Disse muligheder giver forskellige måder at specificere og organisere "
"oplysningerne vist på :guilabel:`Udsendelser` dashboardet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:212
msgid "Filters"
msgstr "Filtre"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:214
msgid ""
"This section of the drop-down mega menu provides different ways to filter "
"email results being shown on the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard in "
"the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app."
msgstr ""
"Dette afsnit af rullemegamenuen giver forskellige måder at filtrere e-"
"mailresultater, der vises på :guilabel:`Udsendelser` dashboardet i "
":guilabel:`E-mailmarketing` appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:0
msgid ""
"View of filters drop-down menu options on the Odoo Email Marketing dashboard."
msgstr ""
"Visning af filterrullemenumuligheder på Odoo E-mailmarketing-dashboardet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:221
msgid ""
"The options are: :guilabel:`My Mailings`, :guilabel:`Sent "
"Date`, :guilabel:`A/B Tests`, :guilabel:`A/B Tests to "
"review`, :guilabel:`Archived`, and :guilabel:`Add Custom Filter`."
msgstr ""
"Mulighederne er: :guilabel:`Mine udsendelser`, :guilabel:`Afsendelsesdato`, "
":guilabel:`A/B-test`, :guilabel:`A/B-test til gennemgang`, "
":guilabel:`Arkiveret` og :guilabel:`Tilføj brugerdefineret filter`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:224
msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Add Custom Filter` is selected, Odoo reveals a pop-up window, "
"with three customizable fields to fill in, in order to create custom filter "
"rules for Odoo to use to retrieve results that fit more specific criteria."
msgstr ""
"Hvis :guilabel:`Tilføj brugerdefineret filter` vælges, viser Odoo et pop-op-"
"vindue med tre tilpasselige felter, der skal udfyldes for at oprette "
"brugerdefinerede filterregler, som Odoo kan bruge til at hente resultater, "
"der passer til mere specifikke kriterier."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:0
msgid ""
"Add custom filter pop-up window that appears in Odoo Email Marketing app."
msgstr ""
"Pop-op-vindue til tilføjelse af brugerdefineret filter, som vises i Odoo E-"
"mailmarketing-appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:232
msgid "Group By"
msgstr "Sortér efter"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:234
msgid ""
"This section of the drop-down mega menu provides different ways to group "
"email results being shown on the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard in "
"the :guilabel:`Email Marketing` app."
msgstr ""
"Dette afsnit af rullemegamenuen giver forskellige måder at gruppere e-"
"mailresultater, der vises på :guilabel:`Udsendelser` dashboardet i "
":guilabel:`E-mailmarketing` appen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:0
msgid ""
"View of the Group By drop-down menu on the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af rullemenuen Gruppér efter i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:241
msgid ""
"Using this section, the data can be grouped by the "
"messages' :guilabel:`Status`, or who it was :guilabel:`Sent By`."
msgstr ""
"Ved hjælp af dette afsnit kan dataene grupperes efter "
"beskeder:guilabel:`Status`, eller hvem de blev :guilabel:`Sendt af`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:244
msgid ""
"There is also the option to group the data by :guilabel:`Sent Period`, which "
"has its own sub-menu of options to choose from. The :guilabel:`Sent Period` "
"options "
"are :guilabel:`Year`, :guilabel:`Quarter`, :guilabel:`Month`, :guilabel:`Week`, "
"and :guilabel:`Day`."
msgstr ""
"Der er også mulighed for at gruppere dataene efter :guilabel:`Sendeperiode`, "
"som har sin egen undermenu med muligheder at vælge imellem. Mulighederne for "
":guilabel:`Sendeperiode` er :guilabel:`År`, :guilabel:`Kvartal`, "
":guilabel:`Måned`, :guilabel:`Uge` og :guilabel:`Dag`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:248
msgid ""
"If none of the above :guilabel:`Group By` options deliver the desired "
"results, click :guilabel:`Add Custom Group` at the bottom of "
"the :guilabel:`Group By` section. Doing so reveals a drop-down menu, wherein "
"custom criteria can be selected and applied, thus delivering any grouping of "
"data that may be desired."
msgstr ""
"Hvis ingen af ovenstående :guilabel:`Gruppér efter` muligheder leverer de "
"ønskede resultater, skal du klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj brugerdefineret "
"gruppe` nederst i afsnittet :guilabel:`Gruppér efter`. Dette afslører en "
"rullemenu, hvor brugerdefinerede kriterier kan vælges og anvendes, og dermed "
"levere enhver ønsket gruppering af data."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:253
msgid "Favorites"
msgstr "Favoritter"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:255
msgid ""
"This section provides the opportunity to save custom filters and/or "
"groupings for future use. To utilize this section, click the :guilabel:`Save "
"current search` field, which reveals additional fields."
msgstr ""
"Dette afsnit giver mulighed for at gemme brugerdefinerede filtre og/eller "
"grupperinger til fremtidig brug. For at bruge dette afsnit skal du klikke på "
"feltet :guilabel:`Gem aktuel søgning`, som afslører yderligere felter."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:0
msgid ""
"View of the Favorites drop-down menu on the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr "Visning af rullemenuen Favoritter i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:263
msgid ""
"Give the favorited filter/grouping a title on the blank line above the "
"checkboxes for :guilabel:`Default filter` and :guilabel:`Shared`."
msgstr ""
"Giv det favoritmarkerede filter/gruppering en titel på den tomme linje over "
"afkrydsningsfelterne for :guilabel:`Standardfilter` og :guilabel:`Delt`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:266
msgid ""
"Ticking the box for :guilabel:`Default filter` makes this favorited filter/"
"grouping the default option. Ticking the box for :guilabel:`Shared` allows "
"other users to see and use this favorited filter/grouping."
msgstr ""
"Markering af feltet for :guilabel:`Standardfilter` gør dette "
"favoritmarkerede filter/gruppering til standardindstillingen. Markering af "
"feltet for :guilabel:`Delt` giver andre brugere mulighed for at se og bruge "
"dette favoritmarkerede filter/gruppering."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:270
msgid ""
"When all desired options are configured, click :guilabel:`Save` to save the "
"filter/grouping in the :guilabel:`Favorites` section of the mega drop-down "
"menu."
msgstr ""
"Når alle ønskede indstillinger er konfigureret, klik på :guilabel:`Gem` for "
"at gemme filteret/grupperingen i afsnittet :guilabel:`Favoritter` i mega-"
"rullemenuen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:274
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/events.rst:99
msgid "Settings"
msgstr "Indstillinger"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:276
msgid ""
"To view and modify the *Email Marketing* settings, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Email Marketing app --> Configuration --> Settings`."
msgstr ""
"For at se og ændre indstillingerne for *E-mailmarketing* skal du navigere "
"til :menuselection:`E-mailmarketing-appen --> Konfiguration --> "
"Indstillinger`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of the Configuration menu with Settings page in the Odoo Email "
"Marketing application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af menuen Konfiguration med siden Indstillinger i Odoo E-"
"mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:283
msgid "On the :guilabel:`Settings` page, there are four features available."
msgstr "På siden :guilabel:`Indstillinger` er der fire tilgængelige funktioner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the Settings page in the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr "Visning af siden Indstillinger i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:289
msgid "The features are:"
msgstr "Funktionerne er:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:291
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Mailing Campaigns`: enables the option to manage mass mailing "
"campaigns."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Mailingkampagner`: aktiverer muligheden for at administrere "
"massemailingkampagner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:292
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Blacklist Option when Unsubscribing`: allows recipients to "
"blacklist themselves from future mailings during the unsubscribing process."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Sortlistemulighed ved afmelding`: giver modtagere mulighed for at "
"sortliste sig selv fra fremtidige mailings under afmeldingsprocessen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:294
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Dedicated Server`: provides the option to utilize a separate, "
"dedicated server for mailings. When enabled, Odoo reveals a new field (and "
"link), in which the specific server configurations must be entered, in order "
"for it to connect properly to Odoo."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Dedikeret server`: giver mulighed for at bruge en separat, "
"dedikeret server til mailings. Når den er aktiveret, viser Odoo et nyt felt "
"(og link), hvor de specifikke serverkonfigurationer skal indtastes, for at "
"den kan forbinde korrekt til Odoo."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:297
msgid ""
":guilabel:`24H Stat Mailing Reports`: allows users to check how well "
"mailings have performed a day after it has been sent."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`24-timers stat mailingrapporter`: giver brugere mulighed for at "
"tjekke, hvor godt mailings har præsteret en dag efter, at den er blevet "
"sendt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:303
msgid "Create an email"
msgstr "Opret en e-mail"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:305
msgid ""
"To create an email, open the :menuselection:`Email Marketing` application, "
"and click the :guilabel:`New` button in the upper-left corner of "
"the :guilabel:`Mailings` dashboard page."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en e-mail skal du åbne applikationen :menuselection:`E-"
"mailmarketing` og klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Ny` i øverste venstre hjørne "
"af dashboardsiden :guilabel:`Mailings`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:308
msgid "Clicking :guilabel:`New` reveals a blank email form."
msgstr "Klik på :guilabel:`Ny` viser en tom e-mailformular."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of a blank email detail form in Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af en tom e-maildetaljeformular i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:314
msgid ""
"On the email form, there are fields for the :ref:`Subject <email_marketing/"
"subject>` and :ref:`Recipients <email_marketing/recipients>` of the email."
msgstr ""
"På e-mailformularen er der felter til :ref:`Emne <email_marketing/subject>` "
"og :ref:`Modtagere <email_marketing/recipients>` af e-mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:317
msgid ""
"Beneath that, there are three tabs: :ref:`Mail Body <email_marketing/"
"mail_body>`, :ref:`A/B Tests <email_marketing/ab_tests>`, and :ref:`Settings "
"<email_marketing/settings_tab>`."
msgstr ""
"Under det er der tre faner: :ref:`Brødtekst <email_marketing/mail_body>`, "
":ref:`A/B-test <email_marketing/ab_tests>` og :ref:`Indstillinger "
"<email_marketing/settings_tab>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:323
msgid "Subject"
msgstr "Emne"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:325
msgid ""
"First, enter a :guilabel:`Subject` to the email. The :guilabel:`Subject` is "
"visible in the recipients' inbox, allowing them to quickly see what the "
"message is about."
msgstr ""
"Indtast først et :guilabel:`Emne` til e-mailen. :guilabel:`Emnet` er synligt "
"i modtagernes indbakke, så de hurtigt kan se, hvad beskeden handler om."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:329
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Subject` field is mandatory. An email can **not** be sent "
"without a :guilabel:`Subject`."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Emne` er obligatorisk. En e-mail kan **ikke** sendes uden "
"et :guilabel:`Emne`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:332
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`(smiley face with a plus sign)` icon at the end of "
"the :guilabel:`Subject` field represents emojis that can be added to "
"the :guilabel:`Subject` field. Clicking that icon reveals a pop-up menu of "
"emojis that can be used."
msgstr ""
"Ikonet :guilabel:`(smiley med et plus-tegn)` i slutningen af feltet "
":guilabel:`Emne` repræsenterer emojis, der kan tilføjes til feltet "
":guilabel:`Emne`. Klik på dette ikon for at åbne en pop-up-menu med emojis, "
"der kan anvendes."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:336
msgid ""
"Beside the :guilabel:`(smiley face with a plus sign)` icon at the end of "
"the :guilabel:`Subject` field is an empty :guilabel:`(star)` icon. When "
"clicked, the :guilabel:`(star)` icon turns gold, and the email is saved as a "
"template in the :guilabel:`Mail Body` tab, which can be used again in the "
"future."
msgstr ""
"Ved siden af ikonet :guilabel:`(smiley med et plus-tegn)` i slutningen af "
"feltet :guilabel:`Emne` er et tomt :guilabel:`(stjerne)`-ikon. Når der "
"klikkes på det, bliver :guilabel:`(stjerne)`-ikonet gyldent, og e-mailen "
"gemmes som en skabelon i fanen :guilabel:`Mail Body`, som kan bruges igen i "
"fremtiden."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:344
msgid "Recipients"
msgstr "Modtagere"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:346
msgid ""
"Beneath the :guilabel:`Subject` field on the email form is "
"the :guilabel:`Recipients` field. In this field, select the recipients of "
"the email. By default, the :guilabel:`Mailing List` option is selected, but "
"clicking the field reveals a drop-down menu of other recipient options."
msgstr ""
"Under feltet :guilabel:`Emne` på e-mail-formularen er feltet "
":guilabel:`Modtagere`. I dette felt vælges modtagerne af e-mailen. Som "
"standard er indstillingen :guilabel:`Mailing List` valgt, men klik på feltet "
"for at åbne en rullemenu med andre modtagerindstillinger."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:350
msgid ""
"With the default :guilabel:`Mailing List` option selected, a specific "
"mailing list **must** be chosen from the adjacent :guilabel:`Select mailing "
"lists` field drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Med standardindstillingen :guilabel:`Mailing List` valgt **skal** der vælges "
"en specifik mailingliste fra rullemenuen i det tilstødende felt "
":guilabel:`Select mailing lists`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:354
msgid ""
"More than one mailing list can be chosen from the :guilabel:`Select mailing "
"lists` field."
msgstr ""
"Der kan vælges mere end én mailingliste fra feltet :guilabel:`Select mailing "
"lists`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:356
msgid "Odoo then sends the email to contacts on that specific mailing list(s)."
msgstr ""
"Odoo sender derefter e-mailen til kontakter på den eller de specifikke "
"mailinglister."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:359
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:825
msgid ":doc:`email_marketing/mailing_lists`"
msgstr ":doc:`email_marketing/mailing_lists`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:361
msgid ""
"When the :guilabel:`Recipients` field is clicked, a drop-down menu of other "
"options is revealed. Each option provides different ways Odoo can create a "
"target audience for the email."
msgstr ""
"Når der klikkes på feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`, vises en rullemenu med "
"andre indstillinger. Hver indstilling giver forskellige måder, hvorpå Odoo "
"kan oprette en målgruppe for e-mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of recipients drop-down menu in the Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af rullemenuen for modtagere i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:368
msgid ""
"Those options (excluding the default :guilabel:`Mailing List`) provide the "
"option to create a more specified recipient filter, in an equation-like "
"format, which appears beneath the :guilabel:`Recipients` field."
msgstr ""
"Disse indstillinger (undtagen standardindstillingen :guilabel:`Mailing "
"List`) giver mulighed for at oprette et mere specificeret modtagerfilter i "
"et ligningslignende format, som vises under feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:372
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Recipients` field options, other than the "
"default :guilabel:`Mailing List` option, are as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Indstillingerne i feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`, ud over "
"standardindstillingen :guilabel:`Mailing List`, er som følger:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:375
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Contact`: ties specifically to the *Contacts* app, and includes "
"all the contacts entered in the database."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Contact`: knytter sig specifikt til *Adressebog*-appen og "
"inkluderer alle kontakter, der er indtastet i databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:377
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Event Registration`: ties specifically to the *Events* app, and "
"provides opportunities to interact with event registrants, in order to "
"communicate important information about the event(s), or nurture other "
"valuable actions, such as post-event surveys, purchases, etc."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Event Registration`: knytter sig specifikt til *Arrangementer*-"
"appen og giver muligheder for at interagere med arrangementstilmeldte for at "
"kommunikere vigtig information om arrangementet/arrangementerne eller fremme "
"andre værdifulde handlinger såsom undersøgelser efter arrangement, køb osv."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:380
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Lead/Opportunity`: ties specifically to records in the *CRM* "
"application, which opens up a number of opportunities to influence sales or "
"purchase decisions."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Lead/Opportunity`: knytter sig specifikt til poster i *CRM*-"
"applikationen, hvilket åbner en række muligheder for at påvirke salgs- eller "
"købsbeslutninger."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:382
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Mailing Contact`: ties specifically to the *Email Marketing* app, "
"and focuses on specific mailing contacts that have been entered in that "
"specific application, and are related to a specific mailing list. These "
"contacts are also unique because they do *not* have their own contact card "
"in the *Contacts* application. This list can be accessed by navigating "
"to :menuselection:`Email Marketing app --> Mailing Lists --> Mailing List "
"Contacts`."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Mailing Contact`: knytter sig specifikt til *E-mailmarketing*-"
"appen og fokuserer på specifikke mailingkontakter, der er indtastet i den "
"specifikke applikation, og som er relateret til en specifik mailingliste. "
"Disse kontakter er også unikke, fordi de *ikke* har deres eget kontaktkort i "
"*Adressebog*-applikationen. Denne liste kan tilgås ved at navigere til "
":menuselection:`E-mailmarketing-app --> Mailinglister --> "
"Mailinglistekontakter`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:387
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Sales Order`: ties specifically to the *Sales* app, and focuses "
"on a specific sales orders in the database."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Sales Order`: knytter sig specifikt til *Salg*-appen og fokuserer "
"på specifikke salgsordrer i databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:391
msgid "Add recipient filter"
msgstr "Tilføj modtagerfilter"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:393
msgid ""
"To add a more specific recipient filter to any :guilabel:`Recipient` option, "
"select any recipient option (other than :guilabel:`Mailing List`), and click "
"the :guilabel:`Modify filter (right-facing arrow)` icon beneath "
"the :guilabel:`Recipient` field to reveal three subsequent filter rule "
"fields, formatted like an equation."
msgstr ""
"For at tilføje et mere specifikt modtagerfilter til en hvilken som helst "
":guilabel:`Modtager`-indstilling vælges en hvilken som helst "
"modtagerindstilling (ud over :guilabel:`Mailing List`), og der klikkes på "
"ikonet :guilabel:`Modificer filter (højrevendt pil)` under feltet "
":guilabel:`Modtager` for at vise tre efterfølgende filterregelfelter, "
"formateret som en ligning."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:398
msgid ""
"It is highly recommended that users implement detailed targeting criteria "
"for the :guilabel:`Recipients` field. Typically, a single line of targeting "
"logic is not sufficient enough for an email campaign."
msgstr ""
"Det anbefales stærkt, at brugere implementerer detaljerede "
"målretningskriterier for feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`. Typisk er en enkelt "
"linje med målretningslogik ikke tilstrækkelig til en e-mail-kampagne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:402
msgid ""
"While the :guilabel:`Mailing List` option is adequate for "
"the :guilabel:`Recipients` field, the :guilabel:`Lead/Opportunity` "
"and :guilabel:`Event Registration` options provide far more detailed "
"targeting criteria, which can be added on top of those seed sources."
msgstr ""
"Mens muligheden :guilabel:`Mailingliste` er passende til feltet "
":guilabel:`Modtagere`, giver mulighederne :guilabel:`Lead/Mulighed` og "
":guilabel:`Eventregistrering` langt mere detaljerede målretningskriterier, "
"som kan tilføjes oven på disse startkilder."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:407
msgid ""
"For example, with the :guilabel:`Lead/Opportunity` option chosen in "
"the :guilabel:`Recipients` field, users can add various custom criteria "
"related to :guilabel:`Created on` "
"dates, :guilabel:`Stages`, :guilabel:`Tags`, :guilabel:`Lost "
"Reasons`, :guilabel:`Sales Teams`, :guilabel:`Active` "
"statuses, :guilabel:`Country`, and so much more."
msgstr ""
"For eksempel kan brugere med muligheden :guilabel:`Lead/Mulighed` valgt i "
"feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere` tilføje forskellige brugerdefinerede kriterier "
"relateret til :guilabel:`Oprettet den`-datoer, :guilabel:`Faser`, "
":guilabel:`Tags`, :guilabel:`Tabte årsager`, :guilabel:`Salgsteams`, "
":guilabel:`Aktiv`-statusser, :guilabel:`Land` og meget mere."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:0
#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of how recipient filters can be customized in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr ""
"Visning af, hvordan modtagerfiltre kan tilpasses i Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:416
msgid ""
"To reveal the sub-menu options within the filter rule fields, click each "
"field, and make the desired selections, until the preferred configuration "
"has been achieved."
msgstr ""
"For at afsløre undermenumulighederne inden for filterregelfeltene skal du "
"klikke på hvert felt og foretage de ønskede valg, indtil den foretrukne "
"konfiguration er opnået."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:419
msgid ""
"The number of :guilabel:`records` in the database that match the configured "
"rule(s) are indicated beneath the configured filter rule(s), in green."
msgstr ""
"Antallet af :guilabel:`poster` i databasen, der matcher den/de konfigurerede "
"regel/regler, vises under den/de konfigurerede filterregel/regler med grønt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:427
msgid ""
"Some sub-menu options in the first rule field allow for a second choice to "
"provide even more specificity."
msgstr ""
"Nogle undermenuindstillinger i det første regelfelt tillader et andet valg "
"for at give endnu mere specificitet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:430
msgid ""
"To the right of each rule, there are three additional options, represented "
"by :guilabel:`➕ (plus sign)`, :guilabel:`(sitemap)`, and :guilabel:`🗑️ "
"(trash)` icons."
msgstr ""
"Til højre for hver regel er der tre yderligere muligheder, repræsenteret af "
"ikonerne :guilabel:`➕ (plustegn)`, :guilabel:`(sitemap)` og :guilabel:`🗑️ "
"(papirkurv)`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:433
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`➕ (plus sign)` icon adds a new node (line) to the overall "
"targeting logic."
msgstr ""
"Ikonet :guilabel:`➕ (plustegn)` tilføjer en ny node (linje) til den "
"overordnede målretningslogik."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:434
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`(sitemap)` icon adds a branch to the node. A branch contains "
"two additional, indented sub-nodes that are related to that specific rule, "
"providing even more specificity to the parent line above it."
msgstr ""
"Ikonet :guilabel:`(sitemap)` tilføjer en gren til noden. En gren indeholder "
"to yderligere, indrykket undernoder, der er relateret til den specifikke "
"regel, hvilket giver endnu mere specificitet til den overordnede linje over "
"den."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:437
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`🗑️ (trash)` icon deletes a specific node (line) in the array "
"of logic."
msgstr ""
"Ikonet :guilabel:`🗑️ (papirkurv)` sletter en specifik node (linje) i "
"logikrækken."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:442
msgid "Mail Body tab"
msgstr "Fanebladet Mailindhold"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:444
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Mail Body` tab, there are a number of pre-configured "
"message templates to choose from."
msgstr ""
"I fanebladet :guilabel:`Mailindhold` er der en række prækonfigurerede "
"beskedskabeloner at vælge imellem."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of the templates in the Mail Body tab in Odoo Email Marketing "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af skabelonerne i fanebladet Mailindhold i Odoo E-mailmarketing-"
"applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:451
msgid ""
"Select the desired template, and proceed to modify every element of its "
"design details with Odoo's drag-and-drop building blocks, which appear on "
"the right sidebar when a template is chosen."
msgstr ""
"Vælg den ønskede skabelon, og fortsæt med at ændre hvert element i dens "
"designdetaljer med Odoos træk-og-slip-byggeklodser, som vises på højre "
"sidepanel, når en skabelon er valgt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of the building blocks in the Mail Body tab in Odoo Email Marketing "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af byggeblokkene i fanebladet Mailindhold i Odoo E-mailmarketing-"
"applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:458
msgid ""
"The features on the sidebar used to create and customize emails are "
"separated into three sections: :guilabel:`Blocks`, :guilabel:`Customize`, "
"and :guilabel:`Design`."
msgstr ""
"Funktionerne på sidepanelet, der bruges til at oprette og tilpasse e-mails, "
"er opdelt i tre sektioner: :guilabel:`Blokke`, :guilabel:`Tilpas` og "
":guilabel:`Design`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:461
msgid ""
"Each building block provides unique features and professional design "
"elements. To use a building block, drag-and-drop the desired block element "
"onto the body of the email being built. Once dropped, various aspects of the "
"building block can be customized."
msgstr ""
"Hver byggeblok giver unikke funktioner og professionelle designelementer. "
"For at bruge en byggeblok skal du trække og slippe det ønskede blokelement "
"ind i brødteksten af den e-mail, der bygges. Når den er sluppet, kan "
"forskellige aspekter af byggeblokken tilpasses."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:466
msgid ""
"To build an email from the ground up, without any building block elements, "
"select the :guilabel:`Plain Text` template. When selected, Odoo provides a "
"completely blank email canvas, which can be customized in a number of way "
"using the front-end rich text editor that accepts forward slash `/` commands."
msgstr ""
"For at bygge en e-mail fra bunden uden nogen byggeblokelementer skal du "
"vælge skabelonen :guilabel:`Almindelig tekst`. Når den er valgt, giver Odoo "
"et helt tomt e-maillærred, som kan tilpasses på en række måder ved hjælp af "
"front-end-richteksteditoren, der accepterer skråstreg `/`-kommandoer."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:471
msgid ""
"When `/` is typed into the blank body of the email, while using "
"a :guilabel:`Plain Text` template, a drop-down menu of various design "
"elements appears, which can be used to create the desired email design."
msgstr ""
"Når `/` indtastes i den tomme brødtekst af e-mailen, mens der bruges en "
":guilabel:`Almindelig tekst`-skabelon, vises en rullemenу med forskellige "
"designelementer, som kan bruges til at skabe det ønskede e-maildesign."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:0
msgid ""
"View of the rich text editor drop-down in the Odoo Email Marketing "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af richteksteditor-rullemenuеn i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:482
msgid "A/B Tests tab"
msgstr "Fanen A/B-tests"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:484
msgid ""
"Initially, when the :guilabel:`A/B Tests` tab is opened on an email form, "
"the only option available is :guilabel:`Allow A/B Testing`. This is **not** "
"a required option."
msgstr ""
"Når fanen :guilabel:`A/B-tests` åbnes i en e-mailformular, er den eneste "
"tilgængelige mulighed først :guilabel:`Tillad A/B-testning`. Dette er "
"**ikke** en påkrævet indstilling."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:487
msgid ""
"If this option is enabled, recipients are only mailed *once* for the "
"entirety of the campaign."
msgstr ""
"Hvis denne indstilling er aktiveret, sendes der kun e-mail til modtagerne "
"*én gang* i hele kampagnens varighed."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:489
msgid ""
"This allows the user to send different versions of the same mailing to "
"randomly selected recipients to gauge the effectiveness of various designs, "
"formats, layouts, content, and so on -- without any duplicate messages being "
"sent."
msgstr ""
"Dette gør det muligt at sende forskellige versioner af samme udsendelse til "
"tilfældigt udvalgte modtagere for at måle effektiviteten af forskellige "
"designs, formater, layouts, indhold osv. -- uden at der sendes duplikerede "
"beskeder."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:493
msgid ""
"When the checkbox beside :guilabel:`Allow A/B Testing` is ticked, "
"an :guilabel:`on (%)` field appears, in which the user determines the "
"percentage of the pre-configured recipients that are going to be sent this "
"current version of the mailing as part of the test."
msgstr ""
"Når afkrydsningsfeltet ved :guilabel:`Tillad A/B-testning` er markeret, "
"vises et :guilabel:`på (%)`-felt, hvor brugeren bestemmer procentdelen af de "
"prækonfigurerede modtagere, der skal modtage denne aktuelle version af "
"udsendelsen som en del af testen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:498
msgid ""
"The default figure in the :guilabel:`on (%)` field is `10`, but that figure "
"can be changed at any time."
msgstr ""
"Standardtallet i feltet :guilabel:`på (%)` er `10`, men dette tal kan ændres "
"når som helst."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:501
msgid "Beneath that, two additional fields appear:"
msgstr "Under det vises to yderligere felter:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:503
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Winner Selection` field provides a drop-down menu of options, "
"wherein the user decides what criteria should be used to determine the "
"\"winning\" version of the email tests that are sent."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Vindervalg` indeholder en rullemenu med valgmuligheder, "
"hvor brugeren bestemmer, hvilke kriterier der skal bruges til at afgøre den "
"\"vindende\" version af de e-mailtests, der sendes."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:507
msgid "The options in the :guilabel:`Winner Selection` field are as follows:"
msgstr "Valgmulighederne i feltet :guilabel:`Vindervalg` er følgende:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:509
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Manual`: allows the user to determine the \"winning\" version of "
"the mailing. This option removes the :guilabel:`Send Final On` field."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Manuel`: giver brugeren mulighed for at bestemme den \"vindende\" "
"version af udsendelsen. Denne mulighed fjerner feltet :guilabel:`Send "
"endelig den`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:511
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Highest Open Rate` (default): the mailing with the highest open "
"rate is determined to be the \"winning\" version."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Højeste åbningsrate` (standard): den udsendelse med den højeste "
"åbningsrate bestemmes som den \"vindende\" version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:513
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Highest Click Rate`: the mailing with the highest click rate is "
"determined to be the \"winning\" version."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Højeste klikrate`: den udsendelse med den højeste klikrate "
"bestemmes som den \"vindende\" version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:515
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Highest Reply Rate`: the mailing with the highest reply rate is "
"determined to be the \"winning\" version."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Højeste svarrate`: den udsendelse med den højeste svarrate "
"bestemmes som den \"vindende\" version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:517
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Leads`: the mailing with the most leads generated is determined "
"to be the \"winning\" version."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kundeemner`: den udsendelse med flest genererede kundeemner "
"bestemmes som den \"vindende\" version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:519
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Quotations`: the mailing with the most quotations generated is "
"determined to be the \"winning\" version."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tilbud`: den udsendelse med flest genererede tilbud bestemmes som "
"den \"vindende\" version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:521
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Revenues`: the mailing with the most revenue generated is "
"determined to be the \"winning\" version."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Indtægter`: den udsendelse med den højeste genererede indtægt "
"bestemmes som den \"vindende\" version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:524
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Send Final On` field allows users to choose a date that is "
"used to know *when* Odoo should determine the \"winning\" email, and "
"subsequently, send that version of the email to the remaining recipients."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :guilabel:`Send endelig den` giver brugerne mulighed for at vælge en "
"dato, der bruges til at vide, *hvornår* Odoo skal bestemme den \"vindende\" "
"e-mail og efterfølgende sende den version af e-mailen til de resterende "
"modtagere."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the A/B Tests tab in Odoo Email Marketing application."
msgstr "Visning af fanen A/B-tests i Odoo E-mailmarketing-applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:532
msgid ""
"To the right of those fields is a :guilabel:`Create an Alternative Version` "
"button. When clicked, Odoo presents a new :guilabel:`Mail Body` tab for the "
"user to create an alternate version of the email to test."
msgstr ""
"Til højre for disse felter findes en :guilabel:`Opret en alternativ version`-"
"knap. Når der klikkes på den, viser Odoo en ny :guilabel:`E-mailtekst`-fane, "
"hvor brugeren kan oprette en alternativ version af e-mailen til test."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:539
msgid "Settings tab"
msgstr "Fanen Indstillinger"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:541
msgid ""
"The options present in the :guilabel:`Settings` tab of the mail form are "
"divided into two sections: :guilabel:`Email Content` "
"and :guilabel:`Tracking`."
msgstr ""
"Muž­nos­ti v kar­tě :guilabel:`Nas­ta­ve­ní` for­mu­lá­ře e-mai­lu jsou roz­dě­le­ny do "
"dvou sek­cí: :guilabel:`Ob­sah e-mai­lu` a :guilabel:`Sle­do­vá­ní`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:545
msgid ""
"The options available in the :guilabel:`Settings` tab vary depending on if "
"the *Mailing Campaigns* feature is activated in :menuselection:`Email "
"Marketing --> Configuration --> Settings`. See :ref:`email_marketing/mailing-"
"campaigns` for more information."
msgstr ""
"Dos­tup­né mož­nos­ti v kar­tě :guilabel:`Nas­ta­ve­ní` se li­ší v zá­vis­los­ti na tom, "
"zda je funk­ce *Mai­lin­go­vé kam­pa­ně* ak­ti­vo­vá­na v :menuselection:`E-"
"mai­lmar­ke­ting --> Kon­fi­gu­ra­ce --> Nas­ta­ve­ní`. Viz :ref:`email_marketing/"
"mailing-campaigns` pro ví­ce in­for­ma­cí."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:549
msgid ""
"Without the *Mailing Campaigns* feature activated, the :guilabel:`Settings` "
"tab on the email form only contains the :guilabel:`Preview "
"Text`, :guilabel:`Send From`, :guilabel:`Reply To`, :guilabel:`Attachments`, "
"and :guilabel:`Responsible` fields."
msgstr ""
"Bez ak­ti­vo­va­né funk­ce *Mai­lin­go­vé kam­pa­ně* ob­sa­hu­je kar­ta "
":guilabel:`Nas­ta­ve­ní` na for­mu­lá­ři e-mai­lu pou­ze po­le :guilabel:`Text "
"náh­le­du`, :guilabel:`Od­e­slat z`, :guilabel:`Od­po­vě­dět na`, "
":guilabel:`Pří­lo­hy` a :guilabel:`Od­po­věd­ný`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of settings tab in Odoo Email Marketing app, without campaign setting "
"activated."
msgstr ""
"Po­hled na kar­tu nas­ta­ve­ní v apli­ka­ci Odoo E-mai­lmar­ke­ting bez ak­ti­vo­va­né­ho "
"nas­ta­ve­ní kam­pa­ně."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:558
msgid "Email content"
msgstr "Ob­sah e-mai­lu"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:560
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Preview Text`: allows the user to enter a preview sentence to "
"encourage recipients to open the email. In most inboxes, this is displayed "
"next to the subject. If left empty, the first characters of the email "
"content appear, instead. The ability to add an emoji in this field is "
"available, as well, via the :guilabel:`(smiley face with a plus sign)` icon."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Text náh­le­du`: umož­ňu­je uži­va­te­li za­dat vě­tu náh­le­du, kte­rá "
"pod­poří pří­jem­ce k ote­vře­ní e-mai­lu. Ve vět­ši­ně schrá­nek se tato vě­ta "
"zo­bra­zu­je ve­dle před­mě­tu. Po­kud zů­sta­ne práz­dná, ob­je­ví se mís­to to­ho pr­vní "
"zna­ky ob­sa­hu e-mai­lu. V tom­to po­li je k dis­po­zi­ci ta­ké mož­nost při­dat emo­ji "
"pro­střed­nic­tvím iko­ny :guilabel:`(smaj­lík se zna­mén­kem plus)`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:564
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Send From`: designate an email alias that displays as the sender "
"of this particular email."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Od­e­slat z`: ur­čí e-mai­lo­vý ali­as, kte­rý se zo­bra­zí ja­ko "
"ode­sí­la­tel to­ho­to kon­krét­ní­ho e-mai­lu."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:566
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Reply To`: designate an email alias to whom all the replies of "
"this particular email are sent."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Od­po­vě­dět na`: ur­čí e-mai­lo­vý ali­as, na kte­rý jsou ode­slá­ny "
"vše­chny od­po­vě­di na ten­to kon­krét­ní e-mail."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:568
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Attach a file`: if any specific files are required (or helpful) "
"for this email, click the :guilabel:`Attachments` button, and upload the "
"desired file(s) to the email."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Při­po­jit sou­bor`: po­kud jsou pro ten­to e-mail vy­žá­do­vá­ny (ne­bo "
"uži­teč­né) ja­ké­ko­liv spe­ci­fic­ké sou­bo­ry, kli­kně­te na tla­čít­ko "
":guilabel:`Pří­lo­hy` a nah­raj­te po­ža­do­va­né sou­bo­ry do e-mai­lu."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:572
msgid "Tracking"
msgstr "Sporing"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:574
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Responsible`: designate a user in the database to be responsible "
"for this particular email."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Od­po­věd­ný`: ur­čí uži­va­te­le v da­ta­ba­zi, kte­rý bu­de od­po­věd­ný za "
"ten­to kon­krét­ní e-mail."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:578
msgid ""
"If the *Mailing Campaign* feature *is* activated, an "
"additional :guilabel:`Campaign` field appears in the :guilabel:`Tracking` "
"section of the :guilabel:`Settings` tab."
msgstr ""
"Po­kud *je* funk­ce *Mai­lin­go­vá kam­paň* ak­ti­vo­vá­na, ob­je­ví se dal­ší po­le "
":guilabel:`Kam­paň` v sek­ci :guilabel:`Sle­do­vá­ní` kar­ty :guilabel:`Nas­ta­ve­ní`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of settings tab in Odoo Email Marketing when campaign setting is "
"activated."
msgstr ""
"Po­hled na kar­tu nas­ta­ve­ní v Odoo E-mai­lmar­ke­tin­gu, když je ak­ti­vo­vá­no "
"nas­ta­ve­ní kam­pa­ně."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:585
msgid ""
"The additional :guilabel:`Campaign` field allows users to attach this "
"particular email to a mailing campaign, if desired."
msgstr ""
"Dal­ší po­le :guilabel:`Kam­paň` umož­ňu­je uži­va­te­lům při­po­jit ten­to kon­krét­ní e-"
"mail k mai­lin­go­vé kam­pa­ni, po­kud si to pře­jí."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:588
msgid ""
"If the desired campaign is not available in the initial drop-down menu, "
"select :guilabel:`Search More` to reveal a complete list of all mailing "
"campaigns in the database."
msgstr ""
"Po­kud nen­í po­ža­do­va­ná kam­paň dos­tup­ná v po­čá­teč­ní roz­ba­lo­va­cí na­bíd­ce, "
"vy­ber­te :guilabel:`Hle­dat ví­ce`, aby se zo­bra­zil úpl­ný se­znam vše­ch "
"mai­lin­go­vých kam­pa­ní v da­ta­ba­zi."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:591
msgid ""
"Or, type the name of the desired mailing campaign in "
"the :guilabel:`Campaign` field, until Odoo reveals the desired campaign in "
"the drop-down menu. Then, select the desired campaign."
msgstr ""
"Ne­bo na­piš­te ná­zev po­ža­do­va­né mai­lin­go­vé kam­pa­ně do po­le :guilabel:`Kam­paň`, "
"do­kud Odoo ne­zo­bra­zí po­ža­do­va­nou kam­paň v roz­ba­lo­va­cí na­bíd­ce. Po­té vy­ber­te "
"po­ža­do­va­nou kam­paň."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:595
msgid "Send, schedule, test"
msgstr "Od­e­slat, nap­lá­no­vat, otes­to­vat"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:597
msgid ""
"Once the mailing is finalized, the following options can be utilized, via "
"buttons located in the upper-left corner of the email form: :ref:`Send "
"<email_marketing/send>`, :ref:`Schedule <email_marketing/schedule>`, "
"and :ref:`Test <email_marketing/test>`."
msgstr ""
"Po do­kon­če­ní mai­lin­gu lze vy­u­žít ná­sle­du­jí­cí mož­nos­ti pro­střed­nic­tvím "
"tla­čí­tek umís­tě­ných v le­vém hor­ním ro­hu for­mu­lá­ře e-mai­lu: :ref:`Od­e­slat "
"<email_marketing/send>`, :ref:`Nap­lá­no­vat <email_marketing/schedule>` a "
":ref:`Tes­t <email_marketing/test>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:604
msgid "Send"
msgstr "Send"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:606
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Send` button reveals a :guilabel:`Ready to unleash emails?` "
"pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Tla­čít­ko :guilabel:`Od­e­slat` zo­bra­zí vy­ska­ko­va­cí ok­no :guilabel:`Jste "
"při­pra­ve­ni vy­pus­tit e-mai­ly?`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of pop-up window that appears when the send button on an email form is "
"clicked."
msgstr ""
"Po­hled na vy­ska­ko­va­cí ok­no, kte­ré se ob­je­ví při klik­nu­tí na tla­čít­ko od­e­slat "
"na for­mu­lá­ři e-mai­lu."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:612
msgid ""
"When the :guilabel:`Send to all` button is clicked, Odoo sends the email to "
"the desired recipients. Once Odoo has sent the mailing, the status changes "
"to :guilabel:`Sent`."
msgstr ""
"Po klik­nu­tí na tla­čít­ko :guilabel:`Od­e­slat vše­m` Odoo ode­šle e-mail "
"po­ža­do­va­ným pří­jem­cům. Po ode­slá­ní mai­lin­gu Odoo se sta­v změ­ní na "
":guilabel:`Od­e­slá­no`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:618
msgid "Schedule"
msgstr "Plan"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:620
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Schedule` button reveals a :guilabel:`When do you want to "
"send your mailing?` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Knappen :guilabel:`Planlæg` åbner et pop op-vindue med :guilabel:`Hvornår "
"vil du sende din udsendelse?`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of pop-up window that appears when the schedule button on an email form "
"is clicked."
msgstr ""
"Visning af pop op-vindue, der vises, når knappen planlæg på en e-"
"mailformular klikkes."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:627
msgid ""
"In this pop-up window, click the :guilabel:`Send on` field to reveal a "
"calendar pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"I dette pop op-vindue skal du klikke på feltet :guilabel:`Send den` for at "
"åbne et kalender pop op-vindue."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:633
msgid ""
"From the calendar pop-up window, select the future date and time for Odoo to "
"send this email. Then, click :guilabel:`✔️ Apply`. When a date and time are "
"chosen, click the :guilabel:`Schedule` button, and the status of the mailing "
"changes to :guilabel:`In Queue`."
msgstr ""
"Fra kalender pop op-vinduet skal du vælge den fremtidige dato og tidspunkt "
"for, hvornår Odoo skal sende denne e-mail. Klik derefter på :guilabel:`✔️ "
"Anvend`. Når en dato og et tidspunkt er valgt, skal du klikke på knappen "
":guilabel:`Planlæg`, og status for udsendelsen ændres til :guilabel:`I kø`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:640
msgid "Test"
msgstr "Test"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:642
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Test` button reveals a :guilabel:`Test Mailing` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Knappen :guilabel:`Test` åbner et pop op-vindue med :guilabel:`Test "
"udsendelse`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of pop-up window that appears when the test button on an email form is "
"clicked."
msgstr ""
"Visning af pop op-vindue, der vises, når testknappen på en e-mailformular "
"klikkes."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:648
msgid ""
"From this pop-up window, enter the email addresses of the contacts to whom "
"Odoo should send this test email in the :guilabel:`Recipients` field. "
"Multiple contacts can be added in this field, if desired."
msgstr ""
"Fra dette pop op-vindue skal du indtaste e-mailadresserne på de kontakter, "
"som Odoo skal sende denne test-e-mail til, i feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`. "
"Der kan tilføjes flere kontakter i dette felt, hvis ønsket."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:652
msgid ""
"Once all the desired email addresses have been entered in "
"the :guilabel:`Recipients` field, click the :guilabel:`Send Test` button."
msgstr ""
"Når alle ønskede e-mailadresser er indtastet i feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`, "
"skal du klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Send test`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:656
msgid ""
"By default, there's a daily limit applied for **all emails** sent throughout "
"**all applications**. So, if there are remaining emails to be sent after a "
"limit has been reached, those mailings are **not** sent automatically the "
"next day. The sending needs to be forced, by opening the email and "
"clicking :guilabel:`Retry`."
msgstr ""
"Som standard er der en daglig grænse for **alle e-mails**, der sendes på "
"tværs af **alle applikationer**. Så hvis der er resterende e-mails, der skal "
"sendes, efter at en grænse er nået, sendes disse udsendelser **ikke** "
"automatisk næste dag. Afsendelsen skal tvinges ved at åbne e-mailen og "
"klikke på :guilabel:`Prøv igen`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:664
msgid "Mailing campaigns"
msgstr "Udsendelseskampagner"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:666
msgid ""
"The *Email Marketing* application provides users with the ability to build "
"mailing campaigns."
msgstr ""
"Applikationen *E-mailmarketing* giver brugerne mulighed for at opbygge "
"udsendelseskampagner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:668
msgid ""
"In order to create and customize mailing campaigns, the *Mailing Campaigns* "
"feature **must** be activated in the *Settings* page of the *Email "
"Marketing* application. To do that, navigate to :menuselection:`Email "
"Marketing app --> Configuration --> Settings`, tick the box "
"beside :guilabel:`Mailing Campaigns`, and click the :guilabel:`Save` button."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette og tilpasse udsendelseskampagner **skal** funktionen "
"*Udsendelseskampagner* aktiveres på siden *Indstillinger* i applikationen *E-"
"mailmarketing*. For at gøre dette skal du navigere til :menuselection:`E-"
"mailmarketing-app --> Konfiguration --> Indstillinger`, sætte flueben ved "
":guilabel:`Udsendelseskampagner` og klikke på knappen :guilabel:`Gem`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the campaign feature setting in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr "Visning af kampagnefunktionsindstillingen i Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:677
msgid ""
"Once the :guilabel:`Mailing Campaigns` feature is activated, a "
"new :guilabel:`Campaigns` menu option appears in the header."
msgstr ""
"Når funktionen :guilabel:`Udsendelseskampagner` er aktiveret, vises en ny "
"menutilvalg :guilabel:`Kampagner` i headeren."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:680
msgid ""
"When that is clicked, Odoo reveals a separate :guilabel:`Campaigns` page, "
"displaying all the mailing campaigns in the database, and the current stage "
"they are in, showcased in a default Kanban view."
msgstr ""
"Når der klikkes på den, åbner Odoo en separat side med "
":guilabel:`Kampagner`, der viser alle udsendelseskampagner i databasen og "
"den aktuelle fase, de er i, vist i en standard Kanban-visning."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the campaign page in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr "Visning af kampagnesiden i Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:688
msgid ""
"This information can also be viewed in a list, by clicking the :guilabel:`☰ "
"(horizontal lines)` icon in the upper-right corner."
msgstr ""
"Disse oplysninger kan også ses i en liste ved at klikke på ikonet "
":guilabel:`☰ (vandrette linjer)` i øverste højre hjørne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:691
msgid ""
"Clicking any campaign from the :guilabel:`Campaigns` page reveals that "
"campaign's form."
msgstr ""
"Klik på en hvilken som helst kampagne fra siden :guilabel:`Kampagner` for at "
"åbne kampagnens formular."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:693
msgid ""
"There are two different ways to create and customize campaigns in the *Email "
"Marketing* application, either directly from the :ref:`Campaigns page "
"<email_marketing/campaign-page>` or through the :ref:`Settings tab "
"<email_marketing/campaign-settings>` on an email form."
msgstr ""
"Der er to forskellige måder at oprette og tilpasse kampagner i applikationen "
"*E-mailmarketing*, enten direkte fra :ref:`Kampagnesiden <email_marketing/"
"campaign-page>` eller via :ref:`Indstillingsfanen <email_marketing/campaign-"
"settings>` på en e-mailformular."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:700
msgid "Create mailing campaign (from campaigns page)"
msgstr "Opret udsendelseskampagne (fra kampagnesiden)"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:702
msgid ""
"When the *Mailing Campaigns* feature is activated, a new *Campaigns* option "
"appears in the header of the *Email Marketing* application. Campaigns can be "
"created directly on the *Campaigns* page in the *Email Marketing* app."
msgstr ""
"Když je aktivována funkce *Mailové kampaně*, objeví se v záhlaví aplikace *E-"
"mailmarketing* nová možnost *Kampaně*. Kampaně lze vytvářet přímo na stránce "
"*Kampaně* v aplikaci *E-mailmarketing*."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:706
msgid ""
"To do that, navigate to :menuselection:`Email Marketing app --> Campaigns --"
"> New`."
msgstr "Přejděte na :menuselection:`E-mailmarketing --> Kampaně --> Nový`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:711
msgid ""
"When the :guilabel:`New` button is clicked in the default Kanban view on "
"the :guilabel:`Campaigns` page, a Kanban card appears in the :guilabel:`New` "
"stage."
msgstr ""
"Po kliknutí na tlačítko :guilabel:`Nový` ve výchozím kanban zobrazení na "
"stránce :guilabel:`Kampaně` se objeví kanban karta ve fázi :guilabel:`Nový`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the campaign pop-up kanban in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr "Zobrazení vyskakovací kanban karty kampaně v Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:718
msgid ""
"New campaign cards can also be made by clicking the :guilabel:`➕ (plus "
"sign)` at the top of any Kanban stage on the :guilabel:`Campaigns` page."
msgstr ""
"Nové karty kampaní lze také vytvořit kliknutím na :guilabel:`➕ (znaménko "
"plus)` v horní části jakékoli kanban fáze na stránce :guilabel:`Kampaně`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:721
msgid ""
"When the new campaign Kanban card appears, the options to enter "
"a :guilabel:`Campaign Name`, a :guilabel:`Responsible`, and :guilabel:`Tags` "
"become readily available."
msgstr ""
"Když se objeví nová kanban karta kampaně, jsou okamžitě k dispozici možnosti "
"zadání :guilabel:`Název kampaně`, :guilabel:`Odpovědná osoba` a "
":guilabel:`Štítky`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:724
msgid ""
"To add the campaign to the Kanban stage, click the :guilabel:`Add` button."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li přidat kampaň do kanban fáze, klikněte na tlačítko "
":guilabel:`Přidat`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:726
msgid "To delete the campaign, click the :guilabel:`🗑️ (trash can)` icon."
msgstr "Chcete-li kampaň smazat, klikněte na ikonu :guilabel:`🗑️ (koš)`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:728
msgid ""
"To further customize the campaign, click the :guilabel:`Edit` button, which "
"reveals the campaign form for additional modifications."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li kampaň dále přizpůsobit, klikněte na tlačítko :guilabel:`Upravit`, "
"které zobrazí formulář kampaně pro další úpravy."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:732
msgid ""
"A :guilabel:`Campaign Name` **must** be entered in the Kanban card, in order "
"for the :guilabel:`Edit` button to reveal the campaign form for further "
"modifications."
msgstr ""
"Do kanban karty **musí** být zadán :guilabel:`Název kampaně`, aby tlačítko "
":guilabel:`Upravit` zobrazilo formulář kampaně pro další úpravy."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:738
msgid ""
"To enter the list view on the :guilabel:`Campaigns` page, click "
"the :guilabel:`☰ (horizontal lines)` icon in the upper-right corner. Doing "
"so reveals all campaign information in a list format."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li zobrazit seznam na stránce :guilabel:`Kampaně`, klikněte na ikonu "
":guilabel:`☰ (vodorovné čáry)` v pravém horním rohu. Zobrazí se všechny "
"informace o kampaních ve formátu seznamu."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the campaign page in list view in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr "Zobrazení stránky kampaní v seznamu v Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:745
msgid ""
"To create a campaign from the :guilabel:`Campaigns` page while in list view, "
"click the :guilabel:`New` button. Doing so reveals a blank campaign form."
msgstr ""
"Chcete-li vytvořit kampaň ze stránky :guilabel:`Kampaně` v zobrazení "
"seznamu, klikněte na tlačítko :guilabel:`Nový`. Zobrazí se prázdný formulář "
"kampaně."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the blank campaign form in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr "Zobrazení prázdného formuláře kampaně v Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:752
msgid ""
"From this campaign form, a :guilabel:`Campaign Name`, "
"a :guilabel:`Responsible`, and :guilabel:`Tags` can be added."
msgstr ""
"V tomto formuláři kampaně lze přidat :guilabel:`Název kampaně`, "
":guilabel:`Odpovědná osoba` a :guilabel:`Štítky`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:755
msgid ""
"At the top of the form, various metric-related smart buttons can be seen "
"that showcase specific analytics related to the campaign. Those smart "
"buttons "
"are: :guilabel:`Revenues`, :guilabel:`Quotations`, :guilabel:`Opportunities`, "
"and :guilabel:`Clicks`."
msgstr ""
"V horní části formuláře jsou vidět různá chytrá tlačítka týkající se metrik, "
"která zobrazují konkrétní analýzy související s kampaní. Tato chytrá "
"tlačítka jsou: :guilabel:`Výnosy`, :guilabel:`Nabídky`, "
":guilabel:`Příležitosti` a :guilabel:`Kliknutí`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:760
msgid ""
"Once a :guilabel:`Campaign Name` is entered and saved, additional buttons "
"appear at the top of the campaign form."
msgstr ""
"Jakmile je zadán a uložen :guilabel:`Název kampaně`, objeví se v horní části "
"formuláře kampaně další tlačítka."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:763
msgid ""
"Those additional buttons are: :guilabel:`Send Mailing` and :guilabel:`Send "
"SMS`."
msgstr ""
"Tato další tlačítka jsou: :guilabel:`Odeslat mailing` a :guilabel:`Odeslat "
"SMS`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:766
msgid "Campaign form"
msgstr "Formulář kampaně"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:768
msgid ""
"On the campaign form (after clicking :guilabel:`Edit` from the Kanban card, "
"or selecting an existing campaign from the :guilabel:`Campaigns` page) there "
"are additional options and metrics available."
msgstr ""
"Ve formuláři kampaně (po kliknutí na :guilabel:`Upravit` z kanban karty nebo "
"výběru existující kampaně ze stránky :guilabel:`Kampaně`) jsou k dispozici "
"další možnosti a metriky."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid "View of the campaign form in Odoo Email Marketing."
msgstr "Visning af kampagneformularen i Odoo E-mailmarketing."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:775
msgid ""
"At the top of the form, various smart buttons can be seen that showcase "
"specific analytics related to the campaign. Those smart buttons "
"are: :guilabel:`Revenues`, :guilabel:`Quotations`, :guilabel:`Opportunities`, "
"and :guilabel:`Clicks`."
msgstr ""
"Øverst i formularen kan der ses forskellige smartknapper, der viser specifik "
"analyse relateret til kampagnen. Disse smartknapper er: "
":guilabel:`Revenues`, :guilabel:`Quotations`, :guilabel:`Opportunities` og "
":guilabel:`Clicks`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:779
msgid ""
"There are also buttons to :guilabel:`Send Mailing`, :guilabel:`Send "
"SMS`, :guilabel:`Add Post`, and :guilabel:`Add Push` (push notification)."
msgstr ""
"Der er også knapper til :guilabel:`Send Mailing`, :guilabel:`Send SMS`, "
":guilabel:`Add Post` og :guilabel:`Add Push` (pushmeddelelse)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:783
msgid ""
"If the :guilabel:`Send Mailing` and :guilabel:`Send SMS` buttons are not "
"readily available, enter a :guilabel:`Campaign Name`, then save (either "
"manually or automatically). Doing so reveals those buttons."
msgstr ""
"Hvis knapperne :guilabel:`Send Mailing` og :guilabel:`Send SMS` ikke er "
"umiddelbart tilgængelige, skal du indtaste et :guilabel:`Campaign Name` og "
"derefter gemme (enten manuelt eller automatisk). Dette afslører disse "
"knapper."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:787
msgid ""
"The status of the campaign can be viewed in the upper-right corner of the "
"campaign form, as well."
msgstr ""
"Kampagnens status kan også ses i øverste højre hjørne af kampagneformularen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:792
msgid "Create mailing campaign (from settings tab)"
msgstr "Oprette mailingkampagne (fra indstillingsfanen)"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:794
msgid ""
"To create a new campaign from the :guilabel:`Settings` tab of a mailing "
"form, click the :guilabel:`Campaign` field, and start typing the name of the "
"new campaign. Then, select either :guilabel:`Create \"[Campaign Name]\"` "
"or :guilabel:`Create and edit...` from the drop-down menu that appears."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette en ny kampagne fra fanen :guilabel:`Settings` i en "
"mailingformular skal du klikke på feltet :guilabel:`Campaign` og begynde at "
"skrive navnet på den nye kampagne. Vælg derefter enten :guilabel:`Create "
"\"[Campaign Name]\"` eller :guilabel:`Create and edit...` fra rullemenuen, "
"der vises."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of the mailing campaign creation in the Settings tab of an email form."
msgstr ""
"Visning af oprettelse af mailingkampagne i fanen Indstillinger i en e-"
"mailformular."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:803
msgid ""
"Select :guilabel:`Create` to add this new mailing campaign to the database, "
"and modify its settings in the future."
msgstr ""
"Vælg :guilabel:`Create` for at tilføje denne nye mailingkampagne til "
"databasen og ændre dens indstillinger i fremtiden."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:806
msgid ""
"Select :guilabel:`Create and Edit...` to add this new mailing campaign to "
"the database, and reveal a :guilabel:`Create Campaign` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Vælg :guilabel:`Create and Edit...` for at tilføje denne nye mailingkampagne "
"til databasen og få vist et pop op-vindue med :guilabel:`Create Campaign`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:None
msgid ""
"View of the email mailing campaign pop-up window in Odoo Email Marketing "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Visning af pop op-vinduet for e-mailmailingkampagne i Odoo E-mailmarketing-"
"applikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:813
msgid ""
"Here, the new mailing campaign can be further customized. Users can adjust "
"the :guilabel:`Campaign Name`, assign a :guilabel:`Responsible`, and "
"add :guilabel:`Tags`."
msgstr ""
"Her kan den nye mailingkampagne tilpasses yderligere. Brugere kan justere "
":guilabel:`Campaign Name`, tildele en :guilabel:`Responsible` og tilføje "
":guilabel:`Tags`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:816
msgid ""
"Buttons to :guilabel:`Add Post` or :guilabel:`Send Push` (push "
"notifications) are also available."
msgstr ""
"Knapper til :guilabel:`Add Post` eller :guilabel:`Send Push` "
"(pushmeddelelser) er også tilgængelige."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:818
msgid ""
"There is also a status located in the upper-right corner of "
"the :guilabel:`Create Campaign` pop-up window."
msgstr ""
"Der er også en status placeret i øverste højre hjørne af pop op-vinduet "
":guilabel:`Create Campaign`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:821
msgid ""
"When all modifications are ready to be finalized, click :guilabel:`Save & "
"Close`. To delete the entire campaign, click :guilabel:`Discard`."
msgstr ""
"Når alle ændringer er klar til at blive afsluttet, skal du klikke på "
":guilabel:`Save & Close`. For at slette hele kampagnen skal du klikke på "
":guilabel:`Discard`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:826
msgid ":doc:`email_marketing/unsubscriptions`"
msgstr ":doc:`email_marketing/unsubscriptions`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:827
msgid ":doc:`email_marketing/lost_leads_email`"
msgstr ":doc:`email_marketing/lost_leads_email`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing.rst:828
msgid ":doc:`email_marketing/analyze_metrics`"
msgstr ":doc:`email_marketing/analyze_metrics`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:3
msgid "Analyze metrics"
msgstr "Analysere målinger"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:7
msgid ""
"In order to properly understand the success or failure of an email marketing "
"campaign, it is necessary to monitor several key metrics. The insights "
"gained from these metrics can then be used to optimize future campaigns. "
"Odoo's **Email Marketing** application tracks several :ref:`key metrics "
"<email-marketing/view-metrics>`, that can be interpreted "
"through :ref:`reports <email_marketing/create_reports>` to improve future "
"campaigns."
msgstr ""
"For at forstå succesen eller fiaskoen for en e-mailmarketingkampagne korrekt "
"er det nødvendigt at overvåge flere nøglemålinger. Indsigterne fra disse "
"målinger kan derefter bruges til at optimere fremtidige kampagner. Odoos **E-"
"mailmarketing**-applikation sporer flere :ref:`nøglemålinger <email-"
"marketing/view-metrics>`, der kan fortolkes gennem :ref:`rapporter "
"<email_marketing/create_reports>` for at forbedre fremtidige kampagner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:16
msgid "View metrics"
msgstr "Vis målepunkter"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:18
msgid ""
"After a mass mail has been sent, the results for that particular mailing are "
"displayed in multiple locations."
msgstr ""
"Efter en massemail er blevet sendt, vises resultaterne for den pågældende "
"udsendelse flere steder."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:21
msgid ""
"To access the metrics for an individual mailing, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Email Marketing app --> Mailings`. Locate the specific "
"mailing in the list view, and use the column headings to view the results "
"for that mailing. Click on one of the mailings in the list to open the "
"record."
msgstr ""
"For at få adgang til målepunkterne for en individuel udsendelse, gå til "
":menuselection:`E-mailmarketing-app --> Udsendelser`. Find den specifikke "
"udsendelse i listevisningen og brug kolonneoverskrifterne til at se "
"resultaterne for den pågældende udsendelse. Klik på en af udsendelserne i "
"listen for at åbne posten."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:25
msgid ""
"At the top of the record, detailed metrics are displayed as smart buttons."
msgstr "Øverst på posten vises detaljerede målepunkter som smarte knapper."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:None
msgid ""
"The smart buttons on a mass mailing, displaying the results of the message."
msgstr ""
"De smarte knapper på en masseudsendelse, der viser resultaterne af beskeden."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:32
msgid "Opened rate"
msgstr "Åbningsrate"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:34
msgid ""
"The percentage of emails opened by recipients, against the total number of "
"sent emails."
msgstr ""
"Procentdelen af e-mails åbnet af modtagere i forhold til det samlede antal "
"sendte e-mails."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:36
msgid ""
"In cases where a reply is expected, such as cold outreach emails, high open "
"rate may indicate the subject line was timely, compelling, and successfully "
"prompted the recipients to view the message."
msgstr ""
"I tilfælde hvor et svar forventes, såsom opsøgende e-mails, kan en høj "
"åbningsrate indikere, at emnelinjen var rettidig, overbevisende og med "
"succes fik modtagerne til at se beskeden."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:39
msgid ""
"In cases where a reply is not expected, such as promotional emails, it may "
"indicate an issue with the email, such as incorrect product links or coupon "
"codes."
msgstr ""
"I tilfælde hvor et svar ikke forventes, såsom salgsfremmende e-mails, kan "
"det indikere et problem med e-mailen, såsom forkerte produktlinks eller "
"rabatkoder."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:42
msgid ""
"In cases where a reply is expected, a low open rate may indicate the subject "
"line failed to capture the recipients' interest or the message ended up in a "
"spam or junk folder. It could also indicate the email ended up in a spam or "
"junk folder."
msgstr ""
"I tilfælde hvor et svar forventes, kan en lav åbningsrate indikere, at "
"emnelinjen ikke formåede at fange modtagernes interesse, eller at beskeden "
"endte i en spam- eller junk-mappe. Det kan også indikere, at e-mailen endte "
"i en spam- eller junk-mappe."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:47
msgid ""
"Emails that consistently land in recipient spam folders could be due to "
"having a poor sender reputation (i.e. high unsubscribe rate, high percentage "
"of past emails marked as spam, etc.), or failing to :doc:`configure the "
"proper DNS records <../../general/email_communication/email_domain>`."
msgstr ""
"E-mails, der konsekvent ender i modtagernes spam-mapper, kan skyldes et "
"dårligt afsenderomdømme (dvs. høj afmeldingsrate, høj procentdel af "
"tidligere e-mails markeret som spam osv.), eller manglende "
":doc:`konfiguration af de korrekte DNS-poster <../../general/"
"email_communication/email_domain>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:53
msgid "Replied rate"
msgstr "Svarrate"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:55
msgid ""
"The percentage of recipients who responded to the email, against the total "
"number of sent emails."
msgstr ""
"Procentdelen af modtagere, der svarede på e-mailen, i forhold til det "
"samlede antal sendte e-mails."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:57
msgid ""
"A high replied rate may indicate the email resonated with recipients, "
"prompting them to take action or provide feedback."
msgstr ""
"En høj svarrate kan indikere, at e-mailen gav genlyd hos modtagerne og fik "
"dem til at handle eller give feedback."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:60
msgid ""
"A low replied rate may suggest the message lacked relevance or did not "
"contain a clear call-to-action."
msgstr ""
"En lav svarrate kan tyde på, at beskeden manglede relevans eller ikke "
"indeholdt en klar opfordring til handling."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:64
msgid "Clicked rate"
msgstr "Klikrate"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:66
msgid ""
"This represents the *Clicked through rate (CTR)*, which measures the "
"percentage of recipients who clicked on a link within the email, against the "
"total number of sent emails."
msgstr ""
"Dette repræsenterer *klikfrekvensen (CTR)*, som måler procentdelen af "
"modtagere, der klikkede på et link i e-mailen, i forhold til det samlede "
"antal sendte e-mails."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:70
msgid ""
"A high |CTR| may indicate the email content was relevant and appropriately "
"targeted. Recipients were motivated to click the links provided, and likely "
"found the content engaging."
msgstr ""
"En høj |CTR| kan indikere, at e-mailens indhold var relevant og passende "
"målrettet. Modtagerne blev motiveret til at klikke på de angivne links og "
"fandt sandsynligvis indholdet engagerende."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:73
msgid ""
"A low |CTR| may indicate issues with either the targeting, or the content "
"itself. Recipients may have been unmotivated by the calls-to-action, if "
"there were any, or the message itself may have been directed toward the "
"wrong audience."
msgstr ""
"En lav |CTR| kan indikere problemer med enten målretningen eller selve "
"indholdet. Modtagerne kan have været umotiverede af opfordringerne til "
"handling, hvis der var nogen, eller beskeden kan have været rettet mod den "
"forkerte målgruppe."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:78
msgid "Received rate"
msgstr "Modtagelsesrate"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:80
msgid ""
"This rate measures the percentage of emails that were **successfully** "
"delivered, against the total number of sent emails."
msgstr ""
"Denne rate måler procentdelen af e-mails, der blev **succesfuldt** leveret, "
"i forhold til det samlede antal sendte e-mails."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:83
msgid ""
"A high received rate can indicate the mailing list used is up-to-date, and "
"the sender authentication is trusted by email providers."
msgstr ""
"En høj modtaget rate kan indikere, at den anvendte mailingliste er "
"opdateret, og at afsenderautentifikationen er betroet af e-mailudbydere."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:86
msgid ""
"A low received rate may indicate issues, either with the mailing list used "
"for the mailing, or with the sender authentication. View the :ref:`email-"
"marketing/deliverability-issues` section for more information."
msgstr ""
"En lav modtaget rate kan indikere problemer enten med mailinglisten, der "
"blev anvendt til mailingen, eller med afsenderautentifikationen. Se "
"afsnittet :ref:`email-marketing/deliverability-issues` for mere information."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:91
msgid "Bounced rate"
msgstr "Bounce-rate"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:93
msgid ""
"This rate measures the percentage of emails that were **unsuccessfully** "
"delivered, and did not enter a recipient's inbox, against the total number "
"of sent emails."
msgstr ""
"Denne rate måler procentdelen af e-mails, der blev **uden succes** leveret "
"og ikke kom ind i en modtagers indbakke, i forhold til det samlede antal "
"sendte e-mails."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:96
msgid ""
"A high bounce rate could indicate issues, either with the mailing list used "
"for the mailing, or with the sender authentication."
msgstr ""
"En høj bounce-rate kan indikere problemer enten med mailinglisten, der blev "
"anvendt til mailingen, eller med afsenderautentifikationen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:99
msgid ""
"A low bounce rate may indicate that the mailing list used is up-to-date, and "
"the sender authentication is trusted by email providers. View "
"the :ref:`email-marketing/deliverability-issues` section for more "
"information."
msgstr ""
"En lav bounce-rate kan indikere, at den anvendte mailingliste er opdateret, "
"og at afsenderautentifikationen er betroet af e-mailudbydere. Se afsnittet "
":ref:`email-marketing/deliverability-issues` for mere information."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:104
msgid ""
"Click on the respective smart buttons to see all the corresponding recipient "
"records that are attributed to each metric. When these filtered records are "
"in view, multiple types of reports can be run for further analysis."
msgstr ""
"Klik på de respektive smarte knapper for at se alle tilsvarende "
"modtagerposter, der tilskrives hver metric. Når disse filtrerede poster er "
"synlige, kan der køres flere typer rapporter til yderligere analyse."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:111
msgid "Create metrics reports"
msgstr "Opret metrics-rapporter"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:113
msgid ""
"Individual metrics can be analyzed by creating a report. To begin, click on "
"the smart button of the desired metric."
msgstr ""
"Individuelle metrics kan analyseres ved at oprette en rapport. Begynd med at "
"klikke på den smarte knap for den ønskede metric."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:116
msgid ""
"Next, click the :icon:`fa-caret-down` :guilabel:`(down arrow)` to the right "
"of the search bar to see a drop-down menu of filtering and grouping "
"parameters."
msgstr ""
"Klik derefter på :icon:`fa-caret-down` :guilabel:`(pil ned)` til højre for "
"søgefeltet for at se en rullemenu med filtrerings- og grupperingsparametre."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:119
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Filters`, located in the left column of the search options, can "
"be used to keep only the results that fit the filter. For example, selecting "
"the *Bounced* filter only shows emails that could not be delivered."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Filtre`, placeret i venstre kolonne af søgemulighederne, kan "
"bruges til kun at beholde de resultater, der passer til filteret. Hvis du "
"f.eks. vælger filteret *Bounced*, vises kun e-mails, der ikke kunne leveres."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:123
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Group By`, found in the middle column, is used to organize the "
"results into groups, and can be used with or without filters."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Gruppér efter`, der findes i midterkolonnen, bruges til at "
"organisere resultaterne i grupper og kan anvendes med eller uden filtre."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:127
msgid ""
"Setting multiple :guilabel:`Group By` options creates nested groups, "
"according to which option is selected first. For example, "
"selecting :guilabel:`Sent Period`, followed by :guilabel:`Add Custom Group --"
"> Responsible`, in the :guilabel:`Group By` column, sorts all results "
"*first* by the sent period, *then* by the team member responsible. This is a "
"useful metric for analyzing who on the team is sending in volume or quantity "
"over a set time period."
msgstr ""
"Indstilling af flere :guilabel:`Gruppér efter`-muligheder opretter "
"indlejrede grupper efter, hvilken mulighed der vælges først. Hvis du f.eks. "
"vælger :guilabel:`Sendt periode` efterfulgt af :guilabel:`Tilføj "
"brugerdefineret gruppe --> Ansvarlig` i kolonnen :guilabel:`Gruppér efter`, "
"sorteres alle resultater *først* efter sendt periode, *derefter* efter det "
"ansvarlige teammedlem. Dette er en nyttig metric til at analysere, hvem i "
"teamet der sender i volumen eller mængde over en fastsat tidsperiode."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:133
msgid ""
"This can be verified by looking at the direction, and order, of the "
"selections in the group tile that appears in the search bar after the "
"selections are made."
msgstr ""
"Dette kan verificeres ved at se på retningen og rækkefølgen af valgene i "
"gruppetilen, der vises i søgefeltet efter, at valgene er foretaget."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:137
msgid ""
"A monthly newsletter has been sent out, and 6.9% of the sent emails were "
"bounced."
msgstr ""
"Et månedligt nyhedsbrev er blevet sendt ud, og 6,9 % af de sendte e-mails "
"blev bouncet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:0
msgid "The metrics smart buttons of the newsletter."
msgstr "Nyhedsbrevets metrics smarte knapper."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:143
msgid ""
"To see what these bounced recipients have in common, the records are grouped "
"using a custom group targeting :guilabel:`Mailing Lists`, which groups all "
"records by the mailing lists they are on. The records are then filtered "
"using a custom filter with the rule `Created on >= 07/01/2024 00:00:00`, to "
"filter by when the mailing list was last checked. This filter only includes "
"recipients that have been created on, or after, July 1st, 2024, in the "
"report."
msgstr ""
"For at se, hvad disse bouncede modtagere har til fælles, grupperes posterne "
"ved hjælp af en brugerdefineret gruppe, der målretter "
":guilabel:`Mailinglister`, som grupperer alle poster efter de mailinglister, "
"de er på. Posterne filtreres derefter ved hjælp af et brugerdefineret filter "
"med reglen `Created on >= 07/01/2024 00:00:00` for at filtrere efter, "
"hvornår mailinglisten sidst blev kontrolleret. Dette filter inkluderer kun "
"modtagere, der er blevet oprettet den 1. juli 2024 eller senere, i rapporten."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:0
msgid "The custom filter creation form."
msgstr "Formularen til oprettelse af brugerdefineret filter."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:153
msgid ""
"Using these configurations, it is evident that all the recipients with "
"bounced emails were added after the list was last checked. Looking closer at "
"the domains, it is evident that each recipient has a malformed email domain "
"(i.e: @yaoo.com instead of @yahoo.com), likely due to a manual entry error "
"while updating the database."
msgstr ""
"Ved hjælp af disse konfigurationer er det tydeligt, at alle modtagere med "
"bouncede e-mails blev tilføjet efter, at listen sidst blev kontrolleret. Ser "
"man nærmere på domænerne, er det tydeligt, at hver modtager har et forkert "
"udformet e-maildomæne (f.eks. @yaoo.com i stedet for @yahoo.com), "
"sandsynligvis på grund af en manuel indtastningsfejl under opdatering af "
"databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:0
msgid "A list of bounced email addresses with malformed email domains."
msgstr ""
"En liste over afviste e-mailadresser med forkert udformede e-maildomæner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:163
msgid ""
"View :doc:`../../essentials/search` for more information about making custom "
"groups and filters."
msgstr ""
"Se :doc:`../../essentials/search` for mere information om at oprette "
"brugerdefinerede grupper og filtre."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:169
msgid "Mass mailing analysis"
msgstr "Analyse af masseudsendelser"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:171
msgid ""
"It is also possible to analyze the success between mailing campaigns by "
"creating a *Mass Mailing Analysis* report. To begin, navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Email Marketing app --> Reporting --> Mass Mailing "
"Analysis`."
msgstr ""
"Det er også muligt at analysere succesen mellem mailingkampagner ved at "
"oprette en rapport for *analyse af masseudsendelser*. For at begynde skal du "
"gå til :menuselection:`E-mailmarketing-appen --> Rapportering --> Analyse af "
"masseudsendelser`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:175
msgid ""
"A dashboard appears displaying a bar chart containing each mailing campaign. "
"By default, :guilabel:`Sent` is selected, displaying the number of sent "
"records on the y-axis. To change the measure, click the :guilabel:`Measures` "
"button, and select the desired measure from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"Et dashboard vises med et søjlediagram, der indeholder hver mailingkampagne. "
"Som standard er :guilabel:`Sendt` valgt, hvilket viser antallet af sendte "
"poster på y-aksen. For at ændre måleenheden skal du klikke på knappen "
":guilabel:`Måleenheder` og vælge den ønskede måleenhed fra rullelisten."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:181
msgid ""
"The following chart displays the number of opened emails from two different "
"mass mailings."
msgstr ""
"Følgende diagram viser antallet af åbnede e-mails fra to forskellige "
"masseudsendelser."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:183
msgid ""
"In this view, it can be seen that the first mass mailing led to a higher "
"opened rate than the second. Because a lower opened rate can sometimes be "
"attributed to a subject line that failed to capture readers' attention, the "
"subject line of each mass mailing can be a good place to begin looking."
msgstr ""
"I denne visning kan det ses, at den første masseudsendelse førte til en "
"højere åbningsrate end den anden. Fordi en lavere åbningsrate nogle gange "
"kan tilskrives en emnelinje, der ikke formåede at fange læsernes "
"opmærksomhed, kan emnelinjen for hver masseudsendelse være et godt sted at "
"begynde at kigge."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:0
msgid ""
"A bar chart displaying the different opened rate between two mass mailing "
"campaigns."
msgstr ""
"Et søjlediagram, der viser den forskellige åbningsrate mellem to "
"masseudsendelseskampagner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:192
msgid ""
"Comparing the two subject lines, it is clear the newsletter's subject line "
"was less engaging, which may have led to the lower opened rate, when "
"compared to the other mass mailing."
msgstr ""
"Når de to emnelinjer sammenlignes, er det klart, at nyhedsbrevets emnelinje "
"var mindre engagerende, hvilket kan have ført til den lavere åbningsrate "
"sammenlignet med den anden masseudsendelse."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:0
msgid "alt text"
msgstr "alt text"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:200
msgid "Deliverability issues"
msgstr "Leveringsproblemer"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:202
msgid ""
"The following define possible reasons for a high bounce rate or low received "
"rate:"
msgstr ""
"Følgende definerer mulige årsager til en høj afvisningsrate eller lav "
"modtagelsesrate:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:204
msgid ""
"Using a mailing list that contains outdated contact information, or "
"malformed email addresses are likely to result in a high bounce rate and/or "
"a low received rate."
msgstr ""
"Brug af en mailingliste, der indeholder forældede kontaktoplysninger eller "
"forkert udformede e-mailadresser, vil sandsynligvis resultere i en høj "
"afvisningsrate og/eller en lav modtagelsesrate."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:206
msgid ""
"Mailings sent using a *From* email address that differs from the sender's "
"domain are likely to bounce with certain email providers due to "
"failing :ref:`DMARC authentication <email-domain-dmarc>`."
msgstr ""
"Udsendelser sendt ved hjælp af en *Fra*-e-mailadresse, der adskiller sig fra "
"afsenderens domæne, vil sandsynligvis blive afvist hos visse e-mailudbydere "
"på grund af fejlende :ref:`DMARC-godkendelse <email-domain-dmarc>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:209
msgid ""
"Failing to :doc:`configure the proper DNS records <../../general/"
"email_communication/email_domain>` can also result in a high bounce rate."
msgstr ""
"Undladelse af at :doc:`konfigurere de korrekte DNS-poster <../../general/"
"email_communication/email_domain>` kan også resultere i en høj "
"afvisningsrate."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:213
msgid ":ref:`Mailing campaigns <email_marketing/mailing-campaigns>`"
msgstr ":ref:`Mailingkampagner <email_marketing/mailing-campaigns>`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/analyze_metrics.rst:214
msgid ":doc:`Manage unsubscriptions <unsubscriptions>`"
msgstr ":doc:`Administrer afmeldinger <unsubscriptions>`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:5
msgid ""
"In Odoo, lost leads are removed from the active *CRM* pipeline, but can "
"still be targeted with the *Email Marketing* application for strategic "
"campaign purposes, such as lost leads reactivation."
msgstr ""
"I Odoo fjernes tabte kundeemner fra den aktive *CRM*-pipeline, men kan "
"stadig målrettes med *E-mailmarketing*-applikationen til strategiske "
"kampagneformål, såsom genaktivering af tabte kundeemner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:8
msgid ""
"A lost leads reactivation email looks at the leads that were lost during a "
"specific period of time, and uses custom filters and lost reasons to exclude "
"undesirable leads from the mailing list."
msgstr ""
"En e-mail til genaktivering af tabte kundeemner ser på de kundeemner, der "
"blev tabt i en bestemt periode, og bruger brugerdefinerede filtre og "
"tabsårsager til at udelukke uønskede kundeemner fra mailinglisten."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:11
msgid ""
"Once a lost leads reactivation email is complete, it can be sent as is, "
"modified and sent to different groups for A/B testing, or saved as a "
"template for later."
msgstr ""
"Når en reaktiverings-e-mail til tabte leads er færdig, kan den sendes som "
"den er, ændres og sendes til forskellige grupper til A/B-test eller gemmes "
"som skabelon til senere brug."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:15
msgid ""
"A warehouse has leftover merchandise from a limited run of items from last "
"year. To help clear out the excess inventory, the warehouse manager creates "
"a lost leads email to reach out to old opportunities that were lost, and "
"inform them that the limited merchandise is back in stock."
msgstr ""
"Et lager har overskudsvarer fra en begrænset produktion af varer fra sidste "
"år. For at hjælpe med at rydde det overskydende lager opretter lagerlederen "
"en e-mail til tabte leads for at kontakte gamle muligheder, der gik tabt, og "
"informere dem om, at de begrænsede varer er tilbage på lager."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:19
msgid ""
"The warehouse manager uses the following filters for a lost leads email:"
msgstr "Lagerlederen bruger følgende filtre til en e-mail til tabte leads:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:21
msgid ":guilabel:`Blacklist` *is* `not set`"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Sortliste` *er* `ikke angivet`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:22
msgid ":guilabel:`Created on` *>=* `01/01/2024 00:00:01`"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Oprettet den` *>=* `01/01/2024 00:00:01`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:23
msgid ":guilabel:`Stage` *is not in* `New`, `Qualified`, or `Won`"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Fase` *er ikke i* `Ny`, `Kvalificeret` eller `Vundet`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:24
msgid ":guilabel:`Lost Reason` *is in* `Not enough stock`"
msgstr ":guilabel:`Tabt årsag` *er i* `Ikke nok på lager`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:25
msgid "and either :guilabel:`Active` *is* `set` or `not set`"
msgstr "og enten :guilabel:`Aktiv` *er* `angivet` eller `ikke angivet`"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"A lost leads reactivation filter list excluding lost reasons like Too "
"Expensive."
msgstr ""
"En filterliste til reaktivering af tabte leads, der udelukker tabte årsager "
"som For dyrt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:32
msgid ""
"As filters are added and removed, pay attention to the :guilabel:`# "
"record(s)` value below the filtering section. This value indicates the total "
"number of records that match the current criteria."
msgstr ""
"Efterhånden som filtre tilføjes og fjernes, skal du være opmærksom på "
"værdien :guilabel:`# post(er)` under filtreringssektionen. Denne værdi "
"angiver det samlede antal poster, der matcher de aktuelle kriterier."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:36
msgid ""
"To view a list of all matching records, click the :guilabel:`# record(s)` "
"text."
msgstr ""
"For at se en liste over alle matchende poster skal du klikke på teksten "
":guilabel:`# post(er)`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid "The # record(s) text is located below the list of Recipient filters."
msgstr "Teksten # post(er) er placeret under listen over modtagerfiltre."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:43
msgid "Minimum requirements"
msgstr "Minimumskrav"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:45
msgid ""
"In order to create and deliver a lost leads reactivation email campaign, the "
"*CRM* and *Email Marketing* applications **must** be :ref:`installed "
"<general/install>` and configured."
msgstr ""
"For at oprette og levere en e-mailkampagne til reaktivering af tabte leads "
"**skal** applikationerne *CRM* og *E-mailmarketing* være :ref:`installeret "
"<general/install>` og konfigureret."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:48
msgid ""
"Here are the minimum necessary filters that pertain to a lost leads "
"reactivation mailing campaign:"
msgstr ""
"Her er de minimalt nødvendige filtre, der vedrører en e-mailkampagne til "
"reaktivering af tabte leads:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:50
msgid ""
"The :ref:`Recipients <email_marketing/recipients_field>` field **must** be "
"set to the *Lead/Opportunity* model."
msgstr ""
"Feltet :ref:`Modtagere <email_marketing/recipients_field>` **skal** være "
"indstillet til modellen *Lead/Mulighed*."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:52
msgid ""
"A :ref:`Blacklist <email_marketing/blacklist_filter>` filter to exclude "
"unsubscribed recipients."
msgstr ""
"Et :ref:`Sortliste <email_marketing/blacklist_filter>`-filter til at "
"udelukke afmeldte modtagere."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:53
msgid ""
"A :ref:`Created on <email_marketing/created_on_filter>` to target leads that "
"were lost during a specific period of time."
msgstr ""
"Et :ref:`Oprettet den <email_marketing/created_on_filter>`-filter til at "
"målrette leads, der gik tabt i en bestemt tidsperiode."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:55
msgid ""
":ref:`Stage <email_marketing/stage_filter>` filter(s) to exclude leads that "
"were already won, or are still active in new stages of the sales pipeline "
"(i.e. *New*, *Qualified*, etc.). These values will be different per "
"organization; however, it's minimally viable to exclude all the leads in the "
"*Won* stage."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Fase <email_marketing/stage_filter>`-filter til at udelukke leads, der "
"allerede er vundet, eller stadig er aktive i nye faser af salgspipeline "
"(dvs. *Ny*, *Kvalificeret* osv.). Disse værdier vil være forskellige pr. "
"organisation; det er dog minimalt levedygtigt at udelukke alle leads i fasen "
"*Vundet*."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:59
msgid ""
"One or more :ref:`Lost Reason <email_marketing/lost_reason_filter>` filters "
"to exclude undesired leads, such as duplicate, spam, or irrelevant records."
msgstr ""
"Et eller flere :ref:`Tabt årsag <email_marketing/lost_reason_filter>`-filtre "
"til at udelukke uønskede leads, såsom duplikater, spam eller irrelevante "
"poster."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:61
msgid ""
"A pair of :ref:`Active <email_marketing/active_filter>` filters to target "
"*both* active and inactive leads."
msgstr ""
"Et par :ref:`aktive <email_marketing/active_filter>` filtre til at målrette "
"mod *både* aktive og inaktive leads."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:65
msgid "Add the necessary filters"
msgstr "Tilføj de nødvendige filtre"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:67
msgid ""
"First, navigate to the :menuselection:`Email Marketing` app, and on "
"the :guilabel:`Mailings` page, click the :guilabel:`New` button in the top-"
"left corner."
msgstr ""
"Naviger først til appen :menuselection:`E-mailmarketing`, og klik på knappen "
":guilabel:`Ny` i øverste venstre hjørne på siden :guilabel:`Udsendelser`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:72
msgid ""
"On the new :guilabel:`Mailings` form, enter an "
"appropriate :guilabel:`Subject` line for the email in the corresponding "
"field. Then, in the :guilabel:`Recipients` field, choose the :guilabel:`Lead/"
"Opportunity` model from the drop-down menu."
msgstr ""
"I den nye :guilabel:`Udsendelser`-formular skal du indtaste en passende "
":guilabel:`Emnelinje` til e-mailen i det tilsvarende felt. Vælg derefter "
":guilabel:`Lead/Mulighed`-modellen fra rullemenuen i feltet "
":guilabel:`Modtagere`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:78
msgid ""
"In the rules section, located beneath the :guilabel:`Recipients` field, "
"click the modify filter (:guilabel:`▶ (triangle pointing right)`) icon to "
"expand the filter rules. Leave the default :guilabel:`Blacklist` rule in "
"place."
msgstr ""
"I regelsektionen, der findes under feltet :guilabel:`Modtagere`, skal du "
"klikke på ikonet for at ændre filter (:guilabel:`▶ (trekant, der peger mod "
"højre)`) for at udvide filterreglerne. Behold standardreglen "
":guilabel:`Sortliste`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:85
msgid "Created on"
msgstr "Oprettet den"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:87
msgid ""
"Begin by clicking :guilabel:`New Rule` beneath the "
"default :guilabel:`Blacklist` rule. Then, click the first field of the new "
"rule that appears, and select the :guilabel:`Created on` parameter from the "
"drop-down menu. With that in place, a specific time period during which the "
"targeted leads were lost can be designated (e.g. 30 days prior, 90 days "
"prior, previous year, etc.)."
msgstr ""
"Begynd med at klikke på :guilabel:`Ny regel` under standardreglen "
":guilabel:`Sortliste`. Klik derefter på det første felt i den nye regel, der "
"vises, og vælg parameteren :guilabel:`Oprettet den` fra rullemenuen. Med "
"dette på plads kan der angives en bestemt tidsperiode, hvor de målrettede "
"leads blev mistet (f.eks. 30 dage før, 90 dage før, forrige år osv.)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:92
msgid ""
"Then, in the second field, select :guilabel:`<= (less than or equal "
"to)`, :guilabel:`>= (greater than or equal to)`, or :guilabel:`is between` "
"as a date operator, in order to frame the time selection chosen in the third "
"field."
msgstr ""
"Vælg derefter i det andet felt :guilabel:`<= (mindre end eller lig med)`, "
":guilabel:`>= (større end eller lig med)` eller :guilabel:`er mellem` som "
"datooperator for at indramme det tidsvalg, der er valgt i det tredje felt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:96
msgid ""
"In the third field, use the calendar popover window to select dates, and "
"click :guilabel:`Apply` to lock in the time range."
msgstr ""
"I det tredje felt skal du bruge kalenderpopover-vinduet til at vælge datoer "
"og klikke på :guilabel:`Anvend` for at låse tidsintervallet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:None
msgid ""
"A custom filter rule setting the time period to be anything before today's "
"date."
msgstr ""
"En brugerdefineret filterregel, der indstiller tidsperioden til at være alt "
"før dags dato."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:104
msgid ""
"When there is more than one rule applied, make sure the statement at the top "
"of the :guilabel:`Recipients` filter list reads: :guilabel:`Match all of the "
"following rules`. If it does not, click on the statement, and "
"select :guilabel:`all` from the drop-down menu (as opposed "
"to :guilabel:`any`)."
msgstr ""
"Når der anvendes mere end én regel, skal du sørge for, at udsagnet øverst på "
"filterlisten :guilabel:`Modtagere` lyder: :guilabel:`Match alle følgende "
"regler`. Hvis det ikke gør det, skal du klikke på udsagnet og vælge "
":guilabel:`alle` fra rullemenuen (i modsætning til :guilabel:`enhver`)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"The statement at the top of the filters list, with the drop-down menu open."
msgstr "Udsagnet øverst på filterlisten med rullemenuen åben."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:116
msgid "Stage"
msgstr "Fase"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:118
msgid ""
"Now, add the :guilabel:`Stage` filter to exclude leads that are in the "
"*New*, *Qualified*, and *Won* stages of the sales pipeline."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj nu :guilabel:`Fase`-filteret for at udelukke leads, der befinder sig "
"i faserne *Ny*, *Kvalificeret* og *Vundet* i salgspipeline."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:122
msgid ""
"This step assumes that the *New*, *Qualified*, and *Won* stages exist in the "
"CRM pipeline; however, stage names may differ from business to business. "
"Refer to the database's actual stage names in the *CRM* app's pipeline to "
"complete this step, accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Dette trin antager, at faserne *Ny*, *Kvalificeret* og *Vundet* findes i CRM-"
"pipeline; fasenavne kan dog variere fra virksomhed til virksomhed. Henvis "
"til databasens faktiske fasenavne i *CRM*-appens pipeline for at fuldføre "
"dette trin i overensstemmelse hermed."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:126
msgid ""
"Begin again by clicking :guilabel:`New Rule` and select :guilabel:`Stage` "
"from the first field's drop-down menu. In the second field, select "
"the :guilabel:`is not in` operator, and in the third field, select "
"the :guilabel:`New`, :guilabel:`Qualified` and :guilabel:`Won` stages to "
"define the rule's parameters."
msgstr ""
"Begynd igen ved at klikke på :guilabel:`Ny regel`, og vælg :guilabel:`Fase` "
"fra det første felts rullemenu. I det andet felt skal du vælge operatoren "
":guilabel:`er ikke i`, og i det tredje felt skal du vælge faserne "
":guilabel:`Ny`, :guilabel:`Kvalificeret` og :guilabel:`Vundet` for at "
"definere reglens parametre."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:131
msgid ""
"When the rule is added in this way, the logic in the third field renders "
"as :code:`OR` (`|`) statements."
msgstr ""
"Når reglen tilføjes på denne måde, gengives logikken i det tredje felt som "
":code:`OR`-udsagn (`|`)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:None
msgid ""
"Include multiple Stages in the filtering rule, using the \"is in\" operator."
msgstr ""
"Inkluder flere faser i filtreringsreglen ved hjælp af operatoren \"er i\"."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:139
msgid ""
"Another way to add *Stage* rules, is to do so on a one-rule-per-row basis "
"using the :guilabel:`contains` or :guilabel:`does not contain` operators, "
"and manually typing out the defining characters in each stage name. This "
"method, however, only allows for one selection at a time, which can be "
"useful for quickly turning on/off filters in the :guilabel:`Search...` bar."
msgstr ""
"En anden måde at tilføje *Fase*-regler på er at gøre det på én-regel-pr.-"
"række-basis ved hjælp af operatorerne :guilabel:`indeholder` eller "
":guilabel:`indeholder ikke` og manuelt skrive de definerende tegn i hvert "
"fasenavn. Denne metode tillader dog kun ét valg ad gangen, hvilket kan være "
"nyttigt til hurtigt at slå filtre til/fra i bjælken :guilabel:`Søg...`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"Three filter rules requiring that the Stage does not contain New, Qualified, "
"or Won."
msgstr ""
"Tre filterregler, der kræver, at fasen ikke indeholder Ny, Kvalificeret "
"eller Vundet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:151
msgid "Lost Reason"
msgstr "Tabte salgsmuligheder"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:153
msgid ""
"Next, add one or more :guilabel:`Lost Reason` rules to exclude leads that "
"should **not** be targeted for specific :doc:`lost reasons <../../sales/crm/"
"pipeline/lost_opportunities>`."
msgstr ""
"Tilføj derefter en eller flere :guilabel:`Tabt årsag`-regler for at udelukke "
"leads, der **ikke** skal målrettes mod specifikke :doc:`tabte årsager <../../"
"sales/crm/pipeline/lost_opportunities>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:156
msgid ""
"To do that, create another :guilabel:`New Rule`, once again. Then, in the "
"rule's first field, select :guilabel:`Lost Reason` from the drop-down menu. "
"For the operator, choose either :guilabel:`is not in` or :guilabel:`does not "
"contain` from the drop-down menu. With either selection, use the third field "
"to enter a lost reason (or multiple lost reasons, depending on your operator "
"choice) to include in the rule."
msgstr ""
"For at gøre det skal du oprette endnu en :guilabel:`Ny regel`. Vælg derefter "
":guilabel:`Tabt årsag` fra rullemenuen i reglens første felt. Vælg enten "
":guilabel:`er ikke i` eller :guilabel:`indeholder ikke` fra rullemenuen som "
"operator. Med begge valg skal du bruge det tredje felt til at indtaste en "
"tabt årsag (eller flere tabte årsager, afhængigt af dit operatorvalg) til at "
"inkludere i reglen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:162
msgid ""
"If choosing the :guilabel:`does not contain` operator, then repeat the "
"preceding steps to add more lost reasons, as needed, where each lost reason "
"occupies one rule row at a time."
msgstr ""
"Hvis du vælger operatoren :guilabel:`indeholder ikke`, skal du gentage de "
"foregående trin for at tilføje flere tabsårsager efter behov, hvor hver "
"tabsårsag optager én regelrække ad gangen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:165
msgid ""
"For more information, refer to the section below outlining how "
"to :ref:`select appropriate lost reasons <email_marketing/"
"select_lost_reasons>`."
msgstr ""
"For mere information, se afsnittet nedenfor, der beskriver, hvordan du "
":ref:`vælger passende tabsårsager <email_marketing/select_lost_reasons>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:None
msgid ""
"A list of filter rules that exclude all lost reasons other than the desired "
"reason."
msgstr ""
"En liste over filterregler, der udelukker alle tabsårsager undtagen den "
"ønskede årsag."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:175
msgid "Active"
msgstr "Aktiv"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:177
msgid ""
"Finally, add a pair of :guilabel:`Active` filters to include both active and "
"inactive leads for the campaign."
msgstr ""
"Til sidst tilføjes et par :guilabel:`Aktiv`-filtre for at inkludere både "
"aktive og inaktive emner i kampagnen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:181
msgid ""
"Adding both active *and* inactive lead records is necessary to capture the "
"full scope of lost leads in the database. Doing one without the other "
"greatly impacts the number of targetable records for the email campaign, and "
"does **not** include a complete or accurate lost leads audience."
msgstr ""
"Det er nødvendigt at tilføje både aktive *og* inaktive emneposter for at "
"fange det fulde omfang af tabte emner i databasen. At gøre det ene uden det "
"andet påvirker antallet af målbare poster til e-mailkampagnen i væsentlig "
"grad og inkluderer **ikke** en komplet eller nøjagtig målgruppe af tabte "
"emner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:186
msgid ""
"First, click the :guilabel:`(Add Branch)` icon on the most recently created "
"rule (e.g. :guilabel:`Lost Reason`), which is the middle of three icons "
"located to the right of the rule row. Doing so adds a pair of :guilabel:`any "
"of` rules. Then, in the top rule's first field of the newly-created branch, "
"select the :guilabel:`Active` parameter from the drop-down menu. The rule "
"then automatically fills out to read: :guilabel:`Active` *is* `set`."
msgstr ""
"Klik først på ikonet :guilabel:`(Tilføj gren)` på den senest oprettede regel "
"(f.eks. :guilabel:`Tabsårsag`), som er det midterste af tre ikoner placeret "
"til højre for regelrækken. Dette tilføjer et par :guilabel:`enhver af`-"
"regler. Vælg derefter parameteren :guilabel:`Aktiv` fra rullemenuen i det "
"første felt i den øverste regel i den nyoprettede gren. Reglen udfyldes "
"derefter automatisk til: :guilabel:`Aktiv` *er* `indstillet`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:192
msgid ""
"For the first field of the bottom rule of the branch, "
"select :guilabel:`Active` from the drop-down menu again. However, this time, "
"select :guilabel:`is not` from the operator drop-down menu in the second "
"field. The rule should then read: :guilabel:`Active` *is not* `set`."
msgstr ""
"Vælg :guilabel:`Aktiv` fra rullemenuen igen i det første felt i den nederste "
"regel i grenen. Denne gang skal du dog vælge :guilabel:`er ikke` fra "
"operatorrullemenuen i det andet felt. Reglen bør derefter læse: "
":guilabel:`Aktiv` *er ikke* `indstillet`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:None
msgid ""
"A pair of Match Any Of filter rules that include both active and inactive "
"leads."
msgstr ""
"Et par Match enhver af-filterregler, der inkluderer både aktive og inaktive "
"emner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:201
msgid "Add body content"
msgstr "Tilføj brødtekst"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:203
msgid ""
"Now, with the domain section of the email campaign complete, create the body "
"content of the email using any of the premade stylized templates, or choose "
"between the :guilabel:`Plain Text` or :guilabel:`Start From Scratch` options "
"for more granular control. For more information, refer to the *Email "
"Marketing* :ref:`documentation on how to create an email <email_marketing/"
"create_email>`."
msgstr ""
"Nu hvor domænedelen af e-mailkampagnen er komplet, skal du oprette "
"brødteksten til e-mailen ved hjælp af en af de færdiglavede stiliserede "
"skabeloner eller vælge mellem mulighederne :guilabel:`Plain Text` eller "
":guilabel:`Start fra bunden` for mere detaljeret kontrol. For mere "
"information, se *E-mailmarketing*-:ref:`dokumentationen om, hvordan du "
"opretter en e-mail <email_marketing/create_email>`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:209
msgid ""
"To save the set of filters for later use, click :guilabel:`Save as Favorite "
"Filter 💾 (floppy disk)`, enter a name (such as `Lost Leads`), and "
"click :guilabel:`Add`."
msgstr ""
"For at gemme sættet af filtre til senere brug skal du klikke på "
":guilabel:`Gem som favoritfilter 💾 (diskette)`, indtaste et navn (som "
"f.eks. `Tabte emner`) og klikke på :guilabel:`Tilføj`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"The Save as Favorite Filter pop-up can save the lost leads criteria for "
"later."
msgstr ""
"Pop-op-vinduet Gem som favoritfilter kan gemme kriterierne for tabte emner "
"til senere."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:217
msgid "Send or schedule"
msgstr "Send eller planlæg"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:219
msgid "Once all the components of the email campaign are complete, either:"
msgstr "Når alle komponenter i e-mailkampagnen er klar, skal du enten:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:221
msgid ""
"click the purple :guilabel:`Send` button at the top-left of the form to "
"immediately send the email; or"
msgstr ""
"klikke på den lilla :guilabel:`Send`-knap øverst til venstre på formularen "
"for at sende e-mailen med det samme; eller"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:223
msgid ""
"click the gray :guilabel:`Schedule` button, located to the right of "
"the :guilabel:`Send` button, to send the email at a future date and time."
msgstr ""
"klikke på den grå :guilabel:`Planlæg`-knap, som ligger til højre for "
":guilabel:`Send`-knappen, for at sende e-mailen på en fremtidig dato og "
"tidspunkt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:227
msgid ""
"Consider using *A/B Testing* to send an alternate version of the email to a "
"percentage of the target leads. This can help determine what subject lines "
"and body content produce the best click-through rates, before sending a "
"final version to the remaining leads."
msgstr ""
"Overvej at bruge *A/B-testning* til at sende en alternativ version af e-"
"mailen til en procentdel af målemner. Dette kan hjælpe med at bestemme, "
"hvilke emnelinjer og brødtekst der giver de bedste klikfrekvenser, før den "
"endelige version sendes til de resterende emner."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:231
msgid ""
"To do so, open the :guilabel:`A/B Tests` tab on the mailing form and check "
"the box next to :guilabel:`Allow A/B Testing`. Then, adjust the parameters "
"as needed, and click :guilabel:`Create an Alternative Version`."
msgstr ""
"For at gøre dette skal du åbne fanen :guilabel:`A/B-tests` på "
"udsendelsesformularen og markere afkrydsningsfeltet ved siden af "
":guilabel:`Tillad A/B-testning`. Juster derefter parametrene efter behov, og "
"klik på :guilabel:`Opret en alternativ version`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"The A/B Tests tab with the Allow A/B Testing box checked to create an "
"alternate version."
msgstr ""
"Fanen A/B-tests med afkrydsningsfeltet Tillad A/B-testning markeret for at "
"oprette en alternativ version."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:242
msgid "Select appropriate lost reasons"
msgstr "Vælg passende tabsårsager"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:244
msgid ""
"When a lead is marked as lost, Odoo recommends selecting a *Lost Reason* to "
"indicate why the opportunity did not result in a sale. Doing so keeps the "
"pipeline organized and reporting data accurate, and generates potential to "
"follow up with the lead in the future."
msgstr ""
"Når et lead markeres som tabt, anbefaler Odoo at vælge en *Tabt-årsag* for "
"at angive, hvorfor muligheden ikke resulterede i et salg. Dette holder "
"pipelinen organiseret og rapporteringsdata nøjagtige, og skaber potentiale "
"for at følge op på leadet i fremtiden."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:248
msgid ""
"If an existing *Lost Reason* is not applicable, users with the necessary "
"permissions can create new ones, which means the lost reasons in a database "
"can vary from organization to organization, and from pipeline to pipeline."
msgstr ""
"Hvis en eksisterende *Tabt-årsag* ikke er anvendelig, kan brugere med de "
"nødvendige tilladelser oprette nye, hvilket betyder at tabt-årsagerne i en "
"database kan variere fra organisation til organisation og fra pipeline til "
"pipeline."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:252
msgid ""
"For more information on *Lost Reasons*, including the creation of them, "
"refer to :doc:`../../sales/crm/pipeline/lost_opportunities`."
msgstr ""
"For mere information om *Tabt-årsager*, herunder oprettelse af dem, se "
":doc:`../../sales/crm/pipeline/lost_opportunities`."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:255
msgid "By default, Odoo includes a few common *Lost Reasons*, such as:"
msgstr ""
"Som standard inkluderer Odoo nogle få almindelige *Tabt-årsager*, såsom:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:257
msgid "*Too expensive*"
msgstr "*For dyrt*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:258
msgid "*We don't have people/skills*"
msgstr "*Vi har ikke folk/kompetencer*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:259
msgid "*Not enough stock*"
msgstr "*Ikke nok lager*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:261
msgid ""
"When determining which reasons to include in a lost leads reactivation "
"email, consider what the email is advertising, in order pinpoint one or more "
"relevant lost reasons. Then, add a rule stating, :guilabel:`Lost Reason` "
"*does not contain* `_____` for every reason in the database, **except** for "
"the relevant one(s)."
msgstr ""
"Når du beslutter, hvilke årsager der skal inkluderes i en reaktiveringsmail "
"til tabte leads, skal du overveje, hvad mailen reklamerer for, for at "
"identificere en eller flere relevante tabt-årsager. Tilføj derefter en "
"regel, der angiver, :guilabel:`Tabt-årsag` *indeholder ikke* `_____` for "
"hver årsag i databasen, **undtagen** den/de relevante."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:267
msgid ""
"If the email advertises a selection of previously-limited merchandise that "
"is now back in stock, it makes sense to target leads with the lost reason: "
"*not enough stock*."
msgstr ""
"Hvis mailen reklamerer for et udvalg af tidligere begrænset merchandise, der "
"nu er tilbage på lager, giver det mening at målrette leads med tabt-årsagen: "
"*ikke nok lager*."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"A list of filter rules that exclude all lost reasons except for Out of Stock."
msgstr ""
"En liste over filterregler, der ekskluderer alle tabt-årsager undtagen Ikke "
"på lager."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:274
msgid ""
"If the email advertises a price reduction, it makes sense to target leads "
"with the lost reason: *too expensive*."
msgstr ""
"Hvis mailen reklamerer for en prisreduktion, giver det mening at målrette "
"leads med tabt-årsagen: *for dyrt*."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:0
msgid ""
"A list of filter rules that exclude all lost reasons except for Too "
"Expensive."
msgstr ""
"En liste over filterregler, der ekskluderer alle tabt-årsager undtagen For "
"dyrt."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:282
msgid "Analyze the results"
msgstr "Analyser resultaterne"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:284
msgid ""
"After sending a lost leads reactivation email, marketing teams can use the "
"smart buttons along the top of the email to analyze the results, and "
"determine follow-up actions."
msgstr ""
"Efter afsendelse af en reaktiveringsmail til tabte leads kan marketingteams "
"bruge de smarte knapper øverst på mailen til at analysere resultaterne og "
"bestemme opfølgende handlinger."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:287
msgid ""
"Clicking on any of the smart buttons opens a list of records matching that "
"button's specific criteria."
msgstr ""
"Klik på en af de smarte knapper for at åbne en liste over poster, der "
"matcher den pågældende knaps specifikke kriterier."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:None
msgid ""
"The Mailing page of a sent email showing the smart buttons along the top of "
"the page."
msgstr ""
"Mailsiden for en afsendt mail, der viser de smarte knapper øverst på siden."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:294
msgid "The smart buttons include:"
msgstr "De smarte knapper inkluderer:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:296
msgid ":guilabel:`Sent`: total number of emails sent."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Sendt`: det samlede antal afsendte mails."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:297
msgid ":guilabel:`Opened`: percentage of recipients that opened the email."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Åbnet`: procentdel af modtagere, der åbnede mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:298
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Replied`: percentage of recipients that replied to the email."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Besvaret`: procentdel af modtagere, der besvarede mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:299
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Clicked`: click-through rate (%) of recipients that clicked on a "
"link in the email."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Klikket`: klikrate (%) for modtagere, der klikkede på et link i e-"
"mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:300
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Leads/Opportunities`: number of leads (or opportunities) that "
"have been created in the *CRM* pipeline, as a result of the email campaign."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Kundeemner/muligheder`: antal kundeemner (eller muligheder), der "
"er blevet oprettet i *CRM*-pipelinen som resultat af e-mailkampagnen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:302
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Quotations`: number of quotations that have been created in the "
"*Sales* application, as a result of the email."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Tilbud`: antal tilbud, der er blevet oprettet i *Salg*-"
"applikationen som resultat af e-mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:304
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Invoiced`: total revenues generated, as a result of the email "
"campaign, via invoices sent to, and paid by, customers. These values are "
"recorded in either the *Invoicing* or *Accounting* application, depending on "
"which app is installed in the database."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Faktureret`: samlede indtægter genereret som resultat af e-"
"mailkampagnen via fakturaer sendt til og betalt af kunder. Disse værdier "
"registreres i enten *Fakturering*- eller *Regnskab*-applikationen, afhængigt "
"af hvilken app der er installeret i databasen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:307
msgid ":guilabel:`Received`: percentage of recipients that received the email."
msgstr ":guilabel:`Modtaget`: procentdel af modtagere, der modtog e-mailen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:308
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Bounced`: percentage of emails that bounced (:dfn:`not "
"delivered`)."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Bounce`: procentdel af e-mails, der blev returneret (:dfn:`ikke "
"leveret`)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:309
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Ignored`: the number of recipients that received the email, but "
"have not interacted with it in a meaningful way (i.e. opened, clicked, etc.)."
msgstr ""
":guilabel:`Ignoreret`: antal modtagere, der modtog e-mailen, men ikke har "
"interageret med den på en meningsfuld måde (dvs. åbnet, klikket osv.)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:313
msgid "Email nurturing"
msgstr "E-mail nurturing"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:315
msgid ""
"*Email nurturing* (sometimes referred to as *lead nurturing*) is the process "
"of sending a series of timely and relevant \"nudge\" emails to connect with "
"a lead, build a deeper relationship, and ultimately convert the lead into a "
"sale."
msgstr ""
"*E-mail nurturing* (nogle gange kaldet *kundeemne nurturing*) er processen "
"med at sende en række rettidige og relevante \"puf\"-e-mails for at forbinde "
"med et kundeemne, opbygge et dybere forhold og i sidste ende konvertere "
"kundeemnet til et salg."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:319
msgid ""
"The point of nurturing is to keep the email campaign \"visible\" or at the "
"top of a lead's inbox, until they are ready to buy."
msgstr ""
"Pointen med nurturing er at holde e-mailkampagnen \"synlig\" eller øverst i "
"et kundeemnes indbakke, indtil de er klar til at købe."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:322
msgid ""
"There are many approaches to effective lead nurturing, but they often "
"involve:"
msgstr ""
"Der er mange tilgange til effektiv kundeemne nurturing, men de involverer "
"ofte:"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:324
msgid "Sending an initial email (such as, a lost leads reactivation email)."
msgstr ""
"Afsendelse af en indledende e-mail (såsom en genaktiverings-e-mail til tabte "
"kundeemner)."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:325
msgid ""
"Sending a follow-up email each week (or according to specific triggers) for "
"the duration of the campaign."
msgstr ""
"Afsendelse af en opfølgnings-e-mail hver uge (eller i henhold til specifikke "
"udløsere) i kampagnens varighed."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:327
msgid ""
"Continuously analyzing results to learn what approaches have resulted in "
"sales."
msgstr ""
"Løbende analyse af resultater for at lære, hvilke tilgange der har "
"resulteret i salg."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:328
msgid ""
"Continuously adjusting the approach to remain \"visible\" at the top of the "
"lead's inbox, and hopefully, get a meaningful response from the lead."
msgstr ""
"Løbende justering af tilgangen for at forblive \"synlig\" øverst i "
"kundeemnets indbakke og forhåbentlig få et meningsfuldt svar fra kundeemnet."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:331
msgid ""
"As a campaign progresses, a marketing team may send different follow-up "
"emails depending on how a lead responded the previous week."
msgstr ""
"Efterhånden som en kampagne skrider frem, kan et marketingteam sende "
"forskellige opfølgnings-e-mails afhængigt af, hvordan et kundeemne har "
"reageret den foregående uge."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:335
msgid ""
"A marketing team wants to advertise a restocking of limited-run merchandise "
"to all leads with a lost reason of *not enough stock*. They develop the "
"following three-week long lead nurturing campaign."
msgstr ""
"Et marketingteam ønsker at annoncere en genopfyldning af merchandise i "
"begrænset oplag til alle kundeemner med en tabt årsag *ikke nok lager*. De "
"udvikler følgende tre uger lang kundeemne nurturing-kampagne."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:339
msgid ""
"**Week 1:** the marketing team sends an initial email, with the subject "
"line: *“Limited run merchandise is back in stock! Act now!”*"
msgstr ""
"**Uge 1:** marketingteamet sender en indledende e-mail med emnelinjen: "
"*\"Merchandise i begrænset oplag er tilbage på lager! Handl nu!\"*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:341
msgid ""
"**Week 2:** the marketing team sends two different emails, depending on how "
"a lead responded."
msgstr ""
"**Uge 2:** marketingteamet sender to forskellige e-mails afhængigt af, "
"hvordan et kundeemne har reageret."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:343
msgid ""
"If a lead ignored the Week 1 email: *“Stock is almost out, did you get "
"yours?”*"
msgstr ""
"Hvis et kundeemne ignorerede uge 1-e-mailen: *\"Lageret er næsten tomt, fik "
"du dit?\"*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:344
msgid ""
"If a lead clicked on the Week 1 email: *\"You still have time to add this to "
"your collection\"*"
msgstr ""
"Hvis et lead klikkede på Week 1-e-mailen: *\"Du har stadig tid til at "
"tilføje dette til din kollektion\"*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:346
msgid ""
"**Week 3:** the marketing team sends a final email to all leads who have not "
"been converted stating: *“20% off, don't miss your last chance to get these "
"items before they're gone!”*"
msgstr ""
"**Uge 3:** marketingteamet sender en endelig e-mail til alle leads, der ikke "
"er blevet konverteret, med følgende tekst: *\"20% rabat, gå ikke glip af din "
"sidste chance for at få disse varer, før de er væk!\"*"

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:349
msgid ""
"Throughout the campaign, the marketing team continuously refers to the smart "
"buttons along the top of the mailing page to see what percentages of leads "
"are opening, clicking on, or ignoring the emails. They also regularly "
"analyze reports on how many opportunities, quotations, and invoices have "
"been generated by the campaign."
msgstr ""
"Gennem hele kampagnen henviser marketingteamet løbende til de smarte knapper "
"øverst på mailinglisten for at se, hvilken procentdel af leads der åbner, "
"klikker på eller ignorerer e-mails. De analyserer også regelmæssigt "
"rapporter om, hvor mange muligheder, tilbud og fakturaer der er blevet "
"genereret af kampagnen."

#: ../../content/applications/marketing/email_marketing/lost_leads_email.rst:355
